title: mom's favorite spareribs
directions: Bring 3/4 cup of vinegar and water to a boil; add ribs.
Cook 10 minutes.
Drain and discard water.
Cut ribs apart into serving pieces.
Put cornstarch in large bowl; add soy sauce and garlic. Mix well.
Turn ribs over and over to coat all pieces.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Heat oil in a large pot.
Add marinated ribs; brown slowly and thoroughly.
Remove from skillet. Pour pineapple syrup, remaining 1/4 cup of vinegar and sugar into skillet.
Stir and cook 1 minute.
Add ribs.
Simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cornstarch mixture left from marinating ribs, pineapple chunks and green bell pepper.
Cook over high heat for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve with hot rice and enjoy!

title: scandinavian cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients in the order given.
Form dough into little balls (size of walnut).
Roll in egg white, then in nuts. Place on greased cookie sheet, then thumbprint them.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Fill with jelly.
For holidays, fill with red and green jelly.

title: mock perogies
directions: Cook lasagna noodles about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cook potatoes, drain, add diced cheese and mash with milk and butter.
Lay 3 noodles in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole that has been well greased.
Spread half potato mixture over noodles.
Add 3 more noodles with remaining potatoes on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Saute onions in butter while casserole is baking.
Top with onions before serving.

title: spaghetti in white clam sauce
directions: Melt butter. Add oil and heat. Saute garlic and clams in hot oil mixture over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in parsley, oregano, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Cook spaghetti and drain well.
Return to pot.
Put sauce on top. Toss lightly and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add all remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Coat 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with cooking spray.
Pour mixture into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about one hour or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center of the loaf comes out clean.
Yields 12 slices.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute seasonings in butter; add crabmeat and season to taste. Add wine and enough bread crumbs to make a thick stuffing.
Stuff mushroom caps and top with bread crumbs.
Lightly oil mushrooms so that they won't wrinkle during cooking.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar well.
Blend Bisquick and flour in along with cinnamon and baking powder. Cook as regular biscuits.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Beat
egg,
sugar,
vanilla
extract
and baking powder together until
smooth and fluffy.	Beat in flour until smooth and well
blended.
Stir
in
walnuts and apples.
Turn into a lightly greased
8-inch pie plate and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Pie will puff
up as it cooks and then collapses as it cools. Serve warm with a scoop of ice milk.

title: horn-toad candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil; remove from heat and add peanut butter.
When dissolved add corn flakes, mixing well. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, water and syrup. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Cook until mixture reaches 232° on candy thermometer.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 cup of flour and sugar.
Add mashed banana, shortening and milk.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed until blended, then on high for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining flour; beat until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into a greased 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes on a wire rack.
Remove from pan and cool thoroughly.
Makes 1 loaf (16 servings).

title: date roll cookies
directions: Cook dates, sugar, butter and eggs slowly for 10 minutes. Turn off heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies and nuts.
Form balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: cubed minute steaks with mushroom sauce
directions: In large skillet with garlic press, press garlic into 2 tablespoons butter.
Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender.
With slotted spoon, remove mushrooms to small bowl and set aside.
In same skillet, in butter, cook steaks until done and remove to platter.
Keep warm.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Spread 1/3 sauce in a ungreased rectangular basking dish (13 x 9 x 2).
Sprinkle garlic salt on chicken tenders.
Insert chicken into uncooked shells.
Stuffing from end of shell to fill if necessary.
Place shells on sauce in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells covering completely.
Sprinkle with cheese. Store no longer than 24 hours in refrigerator covered with aluminum foil.
In freezer, wrap unbaked with aluminum foil. Freeze no longer than 1 month.

title: congealed cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water and let thicken.
Blend remaining ingredients and fold into partially congealed jello. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: baked ham
directions: Make a paste with brown sugar and Coke; spread over ham.
Put in a baking dish, place in a paper bag and bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: spinach souffle salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and heated broth.
Stir until dissolved.
Add salt, lemon juice, salad dressing, chopped spinach, green onion, eggs and bacon.
Mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: smokies in barbecue sauce
directions: Slice a pound of smoked sausage.
Mix remaining ingredients. Cook 1/2 day on low in crock-pot.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients except cinnamon and sugar.
In two separate greased bread pans, divide half of batter into two pans. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Pour in rest of batter into both pans and sprinkle again.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 mins.
Delicious and super simple!

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix yogurt and jello, stirring until well blended.
Use as a dip with fresh fruit of your choice.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in lightly greased casserole and put cheese on top.
Mix soup and wine and spoon on top.
Sprinkle on stuffing mix and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Chill all ingredients before combining.
Serve immediately after adding ginger ale.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Pour dry pudding in bowl and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: jim's mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain. Add 3/4 cup water, taco mix, diced onion, diced pepper, Ro-Tel and chili beans; bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Boil egg noodles and drain. Combine meat mixture and noodles in a casserole dish with 3/4 of the bag of cheese. Mix. Cover top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: acapulco chicken breast
directions: Brown chicken breast in butter or oil until cooked thoroughly in deep skillet.
In saucepan, melt the cheese soup (do not add milk or water).
Add the tomatoes, chopped green onions and salsa. Place chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over chicken and heat in medium oven about 20 minutes until warm. Serve with Spanish rice and enjoy.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Chill dough in icebox for 2 hours.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While cookies are still warm, roll in powdered sugar. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and cornflakes and pour into large casserole (long, narrow type preferable).
Butter casserole well.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Combine crushed cornflakes and melted margarine and spread over casserole.
Return to oven and bake about 15 minutes.

title: black forest cake(from four seasons restaurant)
directions: *To prepare Simple Syrup, boil 1 cup sugar and 2 cups water for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Flavor as desired.

title: mom's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook hen until tender.
Remove from broth and place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with poultry seasoning and bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour 2 cups cold water in broth.
Skim 2 cups off the top.
Let it cool.

title: gourmet chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic until brown.
Saute ground chuck until brown, then drain grease.
Add all ingredients to meat.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bodacious beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook beans with relish and sausage for several hours over low heat, stirring occasionally until beans are tender.
Or cook all ingredients in pressure cooker 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch sticky buns
directions: Night before, grease bottom of the pan.
Line a 9 1/2 x 13-inch dish with pecans.
Place frozen rolls on top.
Cover with brown sugar and butterscotch pudding.
Cut butter into pieces and spread on top.
Cover with waxed paper and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator and let rise until about double in size. Remove waxed paper and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool about 2 or 3 minutes.
Turn pan over on wire rack.
Put waxed paper under.
Serve warm.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Alternate flour and milk mixture; blend well.
Add candy, nuts, coconut and raisins; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake for 3 hours in a 250° oven.
When cake is almost done, heat orange juice and sugar until sugar melts.
Poke hole in cake after it is done. Pour mixture over cake; cool in pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In
2-quart
microwave
casserole, combine all ingredients, except stuffing mix and butter.
Cover and microwave for 5 minutes;
remove
from microwave and stir.
Cover and microwave for
minutes
more.
Remove
from
microwave and cover mixture with
stuffing mix, which has been tossed with butter. Return to microwave and cook for another minute.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients in 1 bowl and blend until smooth.
Place 1/3 of mixture on wax paper and roll into log.
Sprinkle liberally with chili powder and chill.
Do remaining mixture.
Can be frozen.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle meat cubes with salt and pepper.
Saute meat in butter.
Push meat aside; add onions and cook slowly until transparent.
Push aside.
Stir flour into drippings.
Add beef broth and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and add mustard.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Before serving, add mushrooms and sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: grandmother's onion rings
directions: Peel onions; slice in 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness.
Separate rings; keep larger ones to fry, smaller ones for seasoning later on.
Keep ones to fry dry.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Sift flour, salt, sugar and baking powder in a bowl.
Add liquid, a little at a time.
Have butter melted.
Heat fat to 360°.
Drop in a few onions, dipped in batter.
Turn rings once; dip out on paper towels.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Layer hot tamales and then chili, corn and cheese in a baking dish and bake for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mince onion.
Grate cucumber.
Press through sieve.
(I use blender for both of these vegetables.)
The liquid is easily drained by pressing through the sieve.
Add seasonings.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy by hand or mixmaster.
Work in with cucumber mix.
Thin to desired consistency with mayonnaise.
Should stand 24 hours before serving.
Refrigerate. Keeps well.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: blackberry roll
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients.
Work in shortening as for biscuits.
Add enough milk to moisten.
Knead 1 minute and roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with berries.
Sprinkle with sugar and dot with butter.
Roll up and place in buttered baking dish. Boil 1 cup sugar, water and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add vanilla and pour while hot over roll.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done and syrup has thickened.
Serve with milk or ice cream.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until pieces are the size of peas. Sprinkle 1 Tbsp. of water over part of the mixture at a time; gently mix with a fork and push to the side of the bowl. Repeat this process until all of the flour mixture has been moistened. Gather up dough with hands and form into a ball. Divide the dough in half. Roll out on floured paper. Makes two 10 inch crusts.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, pudding and water together and refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Layer in bowl-vanilla wafers, bananas, pudding, vanilla wafers, bananas, pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: glorified rice
directions: Prepare rice and cool. Fold Cool Whip and pineapple into rice. Pour into serving bowl. Garnish with cherries. Chill several hours and serve.

title: glazed fudge brownie pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell for 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add whole eggs, one at a time, beating with each egg.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Alternate flour and sour cream and turn into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first six ingredients together.
Thicken with flour and milk.
Add hard-boiled eggs.
May add 1 to 2 cups milk to make more.

title: coffee cake
directions: Kream buttah 'n sugah reel gud...drap aig in 'n beat...do the same wid the other 'n ...add sour cream 'n vanillah...mix.
Sift flour, bakin' powders 'n salt together 'n add 'n mix.
Spread 1/2 mixture ('n level) in a greasy 9 x 13 pan...now combine nuts, brown sugah and sinnamun.
Sprinkle this over mixture in pan 'n pore rest uv batter over this...level 'n shove the pan in a 350° oven fur an hr.

title: pork chops monterey
directions: Trim excess fat from chops and arrange in baking pan.
Top each chop with an onion slice.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover tightly and bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: instant russian tea mix
directions: Mix together.
Keep in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and brown in frying pan.
Remove pork chops and place in casserole dish.
In frying pan, brown onion until limp.
Add rice; mix and brown.
Add cream of mushroom soup, 1 1/4 cans of water and salt and pepper.
Once all is mixed, add to mixture, Kitchen Bouquet until brown.
Pour mixture over pork chops.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: spiced hot apple cider
directions: Use
30 cup coffee maker.
Place sugar, cinnamon sticks and allspice
in
top
basket.
Pour cider, orange juice and cranberry juice in pot.
Turn on coffee maker and let brew.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. In another bowl, beat pudding and milk until thick.
Add 12 ounce carton Cool Whip.
Add the two together.
Crush 20 ounce package Oreo cookies.
In a flower pot, put a layer of Oreos, then layer of pudding.
Continue but end up with crushed Oreos on top.
Put in some flowers to decorate.

title: cocoa brownie cookies
directions: Cream shortening, light brown sugar, water and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Blend until creamy and blend in eggs.
Add flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop rounded measuring tablespoonfuls, 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies are set.
Cool on baking sheet for 2 minutes before removing.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: sauteed cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Quarter lengthwise and remove seeds.
Cut on slant into diamond shapes.
Melt butter in a large, heavy pan and saute cucumbers in butter for 7 to 10 minutes; add milk and heat to warm.
Toss cheese with flour and add slowly to cucumbers. Season with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, oil and cocoa until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and baking powder and mix until smooth.
Add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Mix on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add chocolate chips. Pour into a greased and lightly floured Bundt baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Invert onto a serving plate and let cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: green party salad
directions: Chill bowl and beaters.
Boil pineapple juice and water to make 4 cups.
Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows.
Set to jelly stage.
Put in mixer and beat until frothy.
Fold in pineapples and other ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: In Dutch oven or large heavy saucepan, lightly brown ground beef.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, frozen vegetables, onion soup mix and sugar; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: fritter batter
directions: Use this batter with chopped or shredded foods like chopped ham, luncheon meat, corn and fruit.
Use 1 cup of food to this recipe.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.

title: sweet orange marmalade
directions: Finely cut or
mince oranges, using a sharp knife, or chop in blender.
Either way remove seeds.
Squeeze lemon and reserve juice.
Add lemon seeds to orange seeds and tie in a piece of cheesecloth.
Combine chopped or slivered oranges, seeds and water.
Add squeezed-out lemon halves.
Let stand overnight.
The next day discard the lemon halves.
Simmer the mixture over low heat for about 1 hour 30 minutes or until peel is soft.
Remove bag of seeds draining thoroughly before discarding.
Yield:
8 oz. jars.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Better if made the day before.

title: vulcan's buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Cream butter and sugar. Add yeast, eggs, oregano, basil, Cheddar cheese, dried tomatoes and milk to butter and sugar mixture. Add flour and salt. Knead 5 to 8 minutes on a floured board. Place dough in greased bowl. Cover and place in a warm place and let rise for 1 hour or until doubled. Stir down risen dough. Turn onto lightly floured surface and form into a smooth loaf. Divide into about 36 balls the size of a walnut. With a finger, punch a hole in the center of each ball and put either one pimento-stuffed olive or a chuck of Feta cheese. Pinch closed. Place 2 balls, pinched side down, in each cup of a greased muffin pan. Mix extra egg white with 1 tablespoon water and brush it on the tops of the buns. Allow to rise 45 minutes or until doubled.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: country style barbecued ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving portions as desired.
Arrange ribs on grill at least 6-inches from medium (ash colored) coals.
Cook 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and cook 5 minutes more.

title: baked halibut with sour cream and cheese
directions: Place
boneless
halibut
in well buttered baking dish. Combine all ingredients (except cheese) and pour over halibut. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over
top
and turn oven broiler on just long enough to brown cheese lightly.
Enjoy!

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice into baking dish. Pour cream of chicken soup over rice. Add 1 cup water. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place chicken over 1/2 cream of chicken soup. Add rest of soup on top of chicken. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: broccoli a la ritz
directions: Boil broccoli as directed.
Drain and place in a casserole dish or rectangular cake pan.
When broccoli is boiling, melt butter over low heat.
Crumble tube of Ritz crackers and add to melted butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Place slices of Velveeta cheese completely over the broccoli.
Add the cracker crumbs/butter mix on top of the cheese.
Pat down.
Bake in oven 18 minutes before serving at 350° or for 4 minutes in microwave.

title: upside down cake
directions: Stir together the brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon and sprinkle half of the mixture over the bottom of a lightly grease 9-inch cake pan.
Arrange mandarin slices in bottom of the pan, sprinkle with the remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix meat ball ingredients. Form into 1 1/2 to 2-inch meat balls. Put into large pot. Add tomato juice and water. Simmer about 45 minutes. Serve with fresh garden salad.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients.
When ingredients are thoroughly blended, add bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Turn mixture into a large loaf pan that is well-greased.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
This freezes well.
Sometimes, I use 2 pans and bake less.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Shred cabbage and onion; steam until tender.
Add sugar and tomato sauce; mix well.
Add to beef.
Stir in cabbage.
Place in bake dish; sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Mix whipped topping, condensed milk and lemonade well by hand. Pour into crust.
Spread evenly. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serve.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter until no longer pink.
Chop onions.
Peel and chop eggplants.
Cook eggplants and onion in pressure cooker for 6 to 8 minutes, longer in open pot.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute, remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter while mixture is hot, stir until all melted.
Then mix in the oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Dissolve jello	in
boiling
water.
Stir
in soup; let cool. When mixture is almost set, fold in mayonnaise, celery, onion and tuna.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: almond butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add salt, almond extract and flour.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and use a cookie press with design.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or so.
They appear not to be done but they will be moist if not over baked.

title: layered cookies
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Put melted butter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle evenly with crackers, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch
chips and nuts.
Over all this, pour the condensed milk.
Bake for 20 or 30 minutes until light brown. Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Chill and serve with chips or vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place cooked rice in medium saucepan.
Add milk and sugar; stir.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to medium; simmer until thick and creamy, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour into medium bowl, stir in vanilla; cool.
Fold in remaining ingredients just before serving.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour and salt.
Combine cocoa.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven and cover with marshmallows. Return to oven about 10 minutes to melt marshmallows.
Then ice with frosting.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with nacho chips or over tacos, etc.

title: mandarin cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and Mandarin oranges and juice until smooth, but no longer.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, or until tests done. (For 2 layers, bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
For a 13 x 9-inch pan, bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.)
Cool 5 minutes in pan, then remove to racks.
Mix pudding mix and pineapple and juice in bowl.
Add Cool Whip; blend thoroughly.
Spread between cake layers and on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Lightly pound chicken breasts.
Layer chicken with cheese and ham.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
In a large skillet, melt butter and brown chicken rolls.
Remove from pan.
Brown mushrooms and onion.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Add milk, stirring constantly over medium heat until thickens.
Remove toothpicks from rolls.
Return chicken to pan.
Cover and simmer approximately 20 minutes.

title: skillet vegetables
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add squash and simmer 10 minutes.
Add drained corn and tomatoes.
Continue to simmer until the squash is soft.
Season to taste.
Serves 6.

title: meal in one casserole
directions: In greased casserole dish, put one row raw sliced potatoes, one row raw sliced onions and one row raw ground chuck (broken in pieces).
Sprinkle with about 1/3 cup uncooked rice.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Repeat once more.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: First, open can of consomme and place in saucepan along with 1 1/4 cups of water; put on to simmer.
Do not boil.
Second, snip steak with scissors about 1/2 finger long.
Third, chop onions. Fourth, in a large skillet, put the butter and chopped onions and saute over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Fifth, add steak; stir into the onions.
Cover and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Sixth, to this mixture, add the flour, tomato paste and mushrooms (including their liquid) and stir all together over low heat.
Seventh, slowly add the hot consomme and sour cream, alternately, stirring after each addition.
Eighth, add soy sauce last.
Serve with rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the white syrup and sugar.
Add the peanut butter, vanilla and cereal.
Pat into bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Frost cookies.

title: white fudge
directions: Bring to a full rolling boil; then let boil on medium for 5 to 6 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix and pour into a greased dish.
Let cool before cutting.

title: club sauce
directions: Grind tomatoes and onions; add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add green and red peppers and cook for 20 minutes more.
Cook longer if you like it thicker, stirring often. Can, seal and process.

title: fudge cake
directions: Bring butter and water to a boil.
Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch.

title: stir-fried chicken and rice
directions: Combine chicken and 2 tablespoons of stir-fry sauce.
Stir pepper into remaining stir-fry sauce and set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a hot skillet over high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Remove.
Heat remaining oil in same pan. Add peas and carrots, onion and salt; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and gently stir in rice to combine.
Stir in chicken and stir-fry sauce; cook and stir over medium-high heat until rice is heated and coated with sauce.
Excellent!

title: honey lemonade
directions: Stir honey and hot water over low heat until blended.
Let cool and add lemon juice and cold water.
Pour into iced glasses

title: lasagne
directions: In Dutch oven or large skillet, cook and stir meats until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes; break up with fork.
Stir in tomato paste, garlic salt, oregano leaves, basil leaves and Ragu spaghetti sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Stir occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes or until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Set aside 1 to 1 1/2 cups meat sauce and 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella cheese.
In ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, alternate layers of 1/3 each noodles, remaining meat sauce, remaining Mozzarella cheese and the cottage cheese mixture.
Spread reserved meat sauce over top; sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle reserved Mozzarella cheese across lasagne.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Cut into 3-inch squares. Makes 8 servings.

title: overnight salad
directions: Cook peas; bring to a boil and drain.
Let cool.
Brown bacon until crispy; remove from heat and break into pieces.
Tear lettuce into pieces and place into large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together.
Mix peas and lettuce together.
Spread mayonnaise mixture over lettuce.
Cover with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle with cheese and bacon.

title: plum pound cake
directions: Mix and cook in stem cake pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: clam dip
directions: Crush crackers and mix all ingredients.
Put in 2 large ovenproof mugs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot on additional Ritz crackers.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in large bowl; set aside.
Cream shortening.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix until well blended.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Spoon half of batter into lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with half of sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 (9-inch) loaf.

title: bean dip
directions: Cook on stove first, then put in crock-pot on low.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add 1/2 package grated cheese.
Put 1/2 package cheese on before serving.

title: low-fat brownie cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Mix brownie mix, egg whites and yogurt.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes or until top looks dry.
Cool 1 to 2 minutes and remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen, approximately 80 calories and 1 gram of fat each.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Peel green shell and pink flesh from firm watermelon rind. Cut in pieces about the size of the last two joints of your little finger. Cut up several lemons in thin slices.
Add same amount of sugar, by weight, as you have fruit.
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Cook very slowly until thick and clear. Seal.

title: grilled venison and vegetables
directions: In a glass bowl or plastic bag, combine vinegar, honey, soy sauce, ketchup, pepper and garlic powder; set aside 1/4 cup. Add meat to bowl or bag, stir or shake to coat.
Cover (or close bag) and refrigerate for 4 hours.
One hour before grilling, toss vegetables with 1/4 cup marinade.
Drain meat, reserving marinade. Thread meat and vegetables alternately on skewers.
Brush with marinade.
Grill over medium hot coals, turning and basting often for 15 to 20 minutes or until meat and vegetables reach desired doneness.

title: perky potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream, onions, salt, pepper, cheese, ham and broccoli.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Drizzle melted butter over flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on package.
Drain well.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain the grease.
Next, puree cooked hamburger in a food processor.
This step is essential, as the texture of the chili is important.

title: gugelor(pound cake)
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar, vanilla sugar and margarine.
To this mixture add the remaining ingredients.
Bake the basic recipe at 350° for 1 hour in a Bundt form which is greased with margarine and sprinkled with breadcrumbs.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix thoroughly egg, milk, apple, sugar, salt, orange juice, orange rind and vanilla.
Stir in 2 cups flour and baking powder. Mix well.
Drop mixture by spoonful into heated oil.
Fry fritters until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels, then dust with powdered sugar.
Yields approximately 5 dozen.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and toss lightly.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs in pan with eggs covered with water for 15 minutes. Let eggs cool.
Slice eggs vertically.
Remove yolks from eggs. Mix egg yolks with all other ingredients, salt and pepper.
Return mixture to center of egg.
May use 1 tablespoon of diced pickles instead of vinegar.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Stew meat with onions.
Combine all ingredients into crock-pot. Heat well.
Serve.
Great for picnics and large gatherings.

title: southwestern lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Grate both cheeses.
Cut green chilies into strips.
Brown hamburger with onion, salt and garlic.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, water, salt, sugar and oregano.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: golden brown oven fried chicken
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt and pepper; mix well.
Dip chicken in sour cream mixture. Dredge in stuffing mix.
Place chicken in greased baking dish. Drizzle with butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hidden valley ranch sausage stars(appetizer)
directions: Note: I put a shake or two of cayenne pepper.

title: frozen buttermilk salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze and cut into squares.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and buttermilk.
Add eggs, butter and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place beef and remaining ingredients in the crock-pot on low all day.
Top with grated cheese and serve with tortilla chips.
This is so easy!
My husband and kids love it.

title: lisa's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter, cocoa and sugar in saucepan.
Add milk.
Bring to boil, stirring often.
When sauce begins to thicken on spoon, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Good over hot buttered biscuits.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips, with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread evenly with wax paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan. Chill 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Bias slice the carrots crosswise about 1/2-inch thick.
Cook in boiling salted water for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain and discard liquid.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, ginger and salt.
Add orange juice.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots, tossing to coat evenly.
Garnish with parsley or orange twist.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: party time cupcake frosting
directions: Mix well with mixer.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg whites separate; set aside and add last.
Melt oleo in hot pumpkin.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add egg whites last. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: white icing
directions: Combine milk and flour in saucepan.
Cook until thick and then cool.
In mixer bowl, cream the sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add milk mixture and beat until fluffy.
A light, not-to-sweet icing.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar with well beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Scald 1/2 cup milk and add butter.
Add to batter while warm.
Bake in 350° oven in a square pan for 25 minutes. When done, add topping made with coconut, brown sugar and butter; brown in broiler.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and parboil in salted water for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
After cooling, scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Mash squash pulp and add onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add bacon bits and butter.
Fill squash shells with mixture; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ham biscuit delight
directions: Leaving rolls together, slice through the middle of all. Combine the next 6 ingredients and spread the top and bottom of rolls with the mixture. Spread the rolls with a layer of meat, then cheese. Place back in pan; cover with foil and heat in a 350° oven.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Combine the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and salt until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Place crust on baking sheet; pour in filling.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 325° oven or until a knife inserted off-center comes out clean.
Combine sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla; carefully spread over pie.
Continue baking for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Chill.
Top with fresh, frozen or canned fruit.
Serves 10.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour over broccoli tops and toss.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Put bacon on top and serve.
Excellent raw vegetable salad.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; cut in butter with pastry cutter or spoon until mixture resembles coarse meal. Stir in pecans.
Spoon apples into a lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon crumb mixture on top.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: lemonade
directions: Combine lemon juice, sugar, and water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Drop sliced lemons into lemonade.
Chill.
Add ice when ready to serve.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir all vegetables in margarine until tender. Remove from heat; stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add water if needed.
Stir in shrimp.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 20 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pizza bread
directions: Defrost bread dough, roll out and place in cookie sheet.
Let rise.
Layer dough with cheese and pepperoni and roll up like a jelly roll.
Let rise again. Bake at 350° approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly, slice and serve.

title: garden veggies parmigiana
directions: Combine vegetables in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with oregano. Pour on the tomato sauce.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella and bake an additional 4 to 5 minutes until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings, 60 calories each.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine in a large pan. Stir in graham cracker crumbs, pecans, coconut, sugar and vanilla.
Add peanut butter and mix well. Roll in balls and lay on waxed paper.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over low heat. Dip each ball in chocolate mixture on the end of toothpick.

title: *company strata
directions: Remove crusts from bread and divide each slice into 4 triangles.
Place half of the bread into bottom of a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place cheese slices on top.
Arrange cooked asparagus on top of cheese.
Place ham on top of asparagus and remaining bread on top of ham.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Whip cream and set aside.
Cream butter; add sugar slowly until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Gently fold whipped cream into batter until well mixed.
Pour into tube pan (layered with wax paper).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place on rack to cool before removing from pan.

title: garlic eye roast(especially for the grill)
directions: Take the roast and make holes in it at different places.
Use the end of a sharp knife (about 1 inch deep).
Insert pieces of garlic into holes (make sure they are well into the meat).
Salt and pepper.
Wrap roast in aluminum foil.
Set it in a deep pan (metal or aluminum is good for the grill).
Cover the grill.
Cook about 2 hours, checking regularly (less if you like your meat rare).

title: pepper relish
directions: Slice and soak the peppers and onions overnight in ice water with 1 cup of salt.
Drain.
Mix the sugars and vinegar; pour over peppers and onions and heat (boil) until juice thickens.
Put in jars and seal.

title: just "soup"
directions: After mixing all ingredients, heat but do not boil.
Serve with crackers.
Hot sauce is optional.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Combine all ingredients together and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Add broccoli and cauliflower if desired.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until blended.
Gradually put in gelatin mixture and remaining water until smooth.
Pour into crust and chill until firm.
Garnish with fruit if desired.
(Okay to use light cream cheese; can use artificial sweetener instead of sugar.)

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 2 hours. Serve with fish, chicken or anything you want.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into well-greased pie pan.
(Square 8-inch pan works well also.)
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until set.
Cool. Spread ice cream over crust.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars. Freeze.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple. Then add sour cream. Put in graham cracker crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, peanut butter and Eagle Brand. Add sugar gradually.
Fold in about 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and grated chocolate. Freeze.
Set out of freezer about 20 minutes before serving.

title: caramel rice crispy squares
directions: Melt caramels, butter and water together in microwave.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: lucy's cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in glass dish.
Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour over margarine.
Pour fruit over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. When done, punch holes in cake with a fork and pour icing over hot cake.

title: irish rag cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Separate egg yolks and whites.
Add egg yolks, flour, baking powder and milk.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Pour into 9-inch cake pans.
Bake between 350° and 375° about 20 or 25 minutes.

title: paste
directions: Put flour in a saucepan. Slowly stir in the water.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Keep stirring until thick and shiny.

title: walnut cluster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine all but nuts.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful.
Bake 11 to 12 minutes. Check in between if cookies are small.
Frost.

title: cowboy corn
directions: Take a	trip
up
into the mountains in the cool, crisp air. Find
a lake with a mountain stream flowing into it with lots of rainbow trout about
inches long.
Say a prayer of thanksgiving and start
fishing.
After
catching
enough fish for a meal, prepare and
cook
them
on an open fire.
As fish are cooking, take a
large
black
(with
use)	iron
skillet. Place about 6 strips of
bacon in the skillet.
When the bacon is about half done, the onion
should go in (so as not to burn the onion). When browned, drain off grease and add corn along with pimentos. Cook the
corn
until
all	is hot.
Place the corn beside the fresh trout
and thank the Lord for His beauty and bounty.

title: choux glorieux
directions: Boil cabbage until very tender in salted water.
Wilt onion in butter, then add cheese in chunks and allow to melt over low heat. When cheese is melted, add the soup and blend into the cheese mixture while still over low heat.
Add the cabbage and mix well. Season to taste.
Put into a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; let stand in cold water overnight.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars.
To each quart, add alum, garlic, dill and red pepper.
Combine vinegar, salt and water; heat to a boil. Fill jars and seal.
Makes 6 to 8 quarts.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Brown ground chuck, onions and bell peppers; drain. Mix all ingredients together, except cheese, and place in a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Then add grated cheese on top and cook until melted.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Break pretzels and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar together; pour over pretzels.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool, then break up with knife.

title: one dish meal
directions: Alternate layers of bread, onion, corn and ham.
Mix egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chuck wagon cream of tomato soup
directions: Heat juice and onion to boiling for 10 minutes.
Remove the onion.
Melt butter; add to the flour.
Add butter and flour to the juice.
Cook until thick.
Add seasonings; remove from heat. Beat in the cold milk.
Heat but do not boil.

title: deep dish apple pudding
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Put them in a deep dish.
Add lemon juice and water.
Mix cinnamon with 1/2 cup of sugar. Sprinkle over apples.
Combine remaining sugar with
flour and salt and work in butter until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Sprinkle over apples and pat smooth.
Bake at 375° until apples are done.

title: blue cheese broccoli
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan, blend in flour, cream cheese and blue cheese.
Add milk and stir till mixture boils.
Stir in broccoli.
Place in 1 qt. casserole and top with Ritz crackers.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Beat eggs with 1 cup sugar until mixture is light and creamy.
Add pumpkin, soda, plain flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts (better without).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
When done, turn onto clean towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up like jelly roll (in towel) until completely cool.
When cool, unroll and spread with mixture of cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Now roll.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions. Beat eggs with soy sauce, salt and pepper. Stir in cooked rice, sprouts and onions. Prepare sauce. Drop mixture by 1/2 cup onto greased griddle. Brown on both sides and serve with sauce.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chicken in cider
directions: Brown chicken in little butter and oil in frypan.
Remove joints from pan and place in large cooking pot.
Cut bacon into small cubes; brown in frying pan, then add to chicken parts. Brown onions; add to chicken and bacon.
Place crushed clove of garlic and sprig of thyme among chicken pieces.
Season with freshly milled pepper and a little salt.
Add bay leaves, cider and stick.
Cover; simmer gently 45 minutes to 1 hour.
During last 15 minutes, add mushrooms; stir into liquid.
Remove chicken etc. on to warm serving dish.
Keep warm.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice in 10 x 14-inch baking dish.
Mix both soups and water together and pour over, mixing until all is wet.
(Add 1/2 package of Lipton onion soup with that.) Put chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with remaining onion soup.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: stuffing for chicken or turkey
directions: Simmer in a little water and butter or oleo the celery and onion until soft.
Add hamburg and simmer until redness is gone. Do not cook the rest.
Soak bread in milk.
Squeeze out excess. Break into pieces.
Add to meat plus graham crackers, egg and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly and stuff into chicken or turkey.
Bake.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Grease with a little of the margarine a 12-cup Bundt pan. Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each biscuit into 3 pieces. Mix together 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a bowl and roll each biscuit piece in it.
Drop biscuit pieces into the Bundt pan.
In a small saucepan, stir together remaining sugar, margarine, cinnamon and the teaspoon vanilla.
Heat on stove until it reaches a boil.
Pour over the biscuit pieces and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Turn onto a plate when done; serve warm.

title: enchiladas acapulco
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup peppers.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and 1/4 pound process cheese spread; continue cooking until process cheese spread is melted.
Dip tortillas in hot oil; drain.
Fill each tortilla with 1/4 cup meat mixture; roll up.
Place, seam side down, in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining process cheese spread; continue baking, uncovered, 5 to 8 minutes or until process cheese spread is melted.
Top with remaining peppers and tomatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: amaretto-almond cake(make day ahead)
directions: In a spring-form pan, fit 1/2 toast into bottom of pan.
Mix water and Amaretto and pour half over toast.
Pour vanilla pudding, then layer toast and pour remaining water and Amaretto mixture, then pour chocolate pudding.
Top with Cool Whip; then sprinkle toasted almonds on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and place on cake pedestal or cake plate.

title: date candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk, water, butter and salt to soft ball stage. Add cherries and dates.
Bring to firm ball stage (245° to 248°). Add marshmallows.
Do not stir.
Cool to room temperature.
Add flavoring.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Add nuts.
Pour into well buttered, shallow pan.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 80 cupcakes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Divide popcorn between 2 cake pans.
Heat sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt, stirring occasionally, until bubbly around edges. Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda (will be foamy).
Cover popcorn with caramel sauce and bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Grate cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, onion and garlic salt.
Place rolls in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage on dough.
Cover with cheese.
Pour eggs, milk, onion and garlic salt mixture on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Use fresh
beans,
if you like.
You may also use tomatoes, if you
like.	I don't put green pepper in it.
Put less pepper in; add a little more sugar.
The colder you get this, the better it is.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Soften cream cheese, then add all of the other ingredients and serve with cauliflower or other vegetable.

title: chocolate ecstasy
directions: Make the cake according to package instructions.
When cool, break into pieces, 2 to 3 inches in size.
Mix pudding as directed on box and blend in the Kahlua.

In a large punch bowl or clear glass baking dish place a layer of about 1/2 of the cake pieces. Cover with half of the pudding mixture, then 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Sprinkle on 1/2 of the crushed Heath bars.
(Crushing is easier when you freeze the bars first.)
Repeat layers ending with Cool Whip and Heath bars.
Refrigerate.

title: egg and cheese bake
directions: Cube bread.
Slice kielbasa thin.
Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with cheese, then kielbasa.
Beat together eggs, mustard, soup and milk (I use a blender).
Pour over bread, cheese and kielbasa.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake next day at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add sugar and Cool Whip.
In pan, place a layer of broken graham crackers and a layer of pudding mixture until all is used.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over mixture.
Top with pecans.
Chill.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine pie filling mix, 1/2 cup of the sugar and 3/4 cup of the water in a medium saucepan.
Blend in egg yolks and remaining water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat. Stir in lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Cool filling 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Place crust on baking sheet and pour in filling.

title: italian vegetables
directions: Mix all together and
put
dressing
over it all.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap.
Microwave
at
High for 6 to 7 minutes or until vegetables
are
tender-crisp.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Beat egg yolks slightly, add with milk to sugar and cook until thickens.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Put into baked crust.

title: roasted root vegetables
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Put all the vegetables and the herb sprigs in a large baking dish. Season well with salt and black pepper, drizzle generously with olive oil, and toss them with your hands to coat them evenly. Put the baking dish in the preheated oven and cook, stirring the vegetables occasionally, until they are tender and golden brown, about 45 minutes. Serve the vegetables from their baking dish or transfer them to a platter to accompany a roasted main course.

title: cindy bazin's corn chowder
directions: In a soup kettle, saute potatoes, onions, butter and broth for about ten minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook until the potatoes are fully cooked.

title: peach sour cream cake
directions: Melt the butter and mix with cake mix.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan slightly onto sides.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: consomme rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet and add uncooked rice.
Stir until all kernels are browned.
Reduce heat if browning too fast.

title: apricot nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch pan.
Cover apricots in lukewarm water for 30 minutes; drain.
Remove zest from 1/2 orange with vegetable peeler.
Cut orange in 1/2 and squeeze juices from both halves.
Grind apricots, orange zest and raisins in processor.
Add enough boiling water to orange juice to make 1 cup and pour into bowl with ground fruit.
Stir sugar and butter; beat in eggs.
In separate bowl, stir flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and walnuts.
Add to fruit.
Mix with vanilla.
Pour into pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: crispy ranch chicken
directions: Will also need 1 plastic bag.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Beat in eggs. Add flour, baking soda and powder, salt and cinnamon, beating well after each addition. Stir in morsels, nuts and apples. Mixture will be thick. Press mixture into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill, preferably overnight.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix well and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll 1/4 inch thick or more.
Bake 350° for 20 minutes. With no refrigeration at the time, this was mostly a winter cookie. We would chill it over night and cook the next day.
Also, this cookie is high in energy.

title: frozen lemon squares
directions: Combine butter, crumbs and sugar.
Press into an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in milk, then lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into crust.
Top with whipped topping.
Freeze until firm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, sour cream, oil, eggs and milk. Add vanilla and beat again. Fold in floured nuts.
Pour half of the batter into tube pan. Combine cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over first half of batter, then add remaining batter.
Bake for 50 minutes or until done at 300°.

title: bacon and broccoli
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill; serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and put on a pizza pan or cookie sheet, overlapped.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with cream cheese.
Add assorted fruit and put jam on top.
Slice and eat.
Mix 1 teaspoon water with jam before putting on top of fruit.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix and cool until thickened first 4 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients.
When set, frost with Cool Whip mixed with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Bake cake mix according to box directions.
When cool, tear up cake and layer in large bowl with other ingredients: cake, then pudding, candy bars and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, finishing with Cool Whip topped with enough candy for decoration.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine in top of double boiler.
Add flour, seasonings and milk.
Cook until thick and add 1 cup grated sharp cheese.
In greased baking dish, put a layer of asparagus, layer of sauce and layer of cracker crumbs.
Repeat and top with more grated cheese. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Boil rice, soup and water for 7 minutes.
Brown sausage.
Lift out with slotted spoon.
Add sausage to above mixture.
Brown in sausage drippings the celery and onion.
Add to rice mixture.
Put into casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Mix all together and roll as with regular pie crust.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside. Put walnuts into food processor. Pulse 4 to 10 seconds. Add nuts to dry ingredients. Put into processor sugar, butter, egg, bananas, and milk. Pulse.
Add to dry ingredients. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350 degrees till brown.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chopped onion, green pepper strips and minced garlic in 2 tablespoons of salad oil or olive oil in skillet.
Remove and lay aside for later use.
Add remaining oil to skillet.
Place pieces of chicken in paper bag with flour and shake.
Remove chicken and place in skillet.
Fry until golden brown.
Return browned onion, peppers and garlic to the skillet.
Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, spices, pimiento and mushrooms.
Add to chicken. Simmer, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender. Serve sauce over chicken.

title: shrimp south louisiana
directions: Combine Crisco shortening and flour in large saucepan.
Cook and stir until dark brown.
Add onions, green onions, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add shrimp.
Cook 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar, peanut butter and nuts.
Butter hands and pinch off a ball 1-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: brandy fruit compote
directions: Defrost unopened can of orange juice concentrate.
Wash and hull berries and blot dry on paper towels. Peel peaches, cut into halves and remove pits.
Place in a shallow crystal bowl. Sprinkle with sugar. Cover with strawberries and sprinkle lightly with sugar to taste.
Stir brandy into undiluted orange juice concentrate.
Pour over fruits and mix gently.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Stir occasionally. Serve in individual small bowls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: louisiana pralines
directions: Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper.
In a heavy, 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Add pecans.
Cook over low heat to soft ball stage (234° on candy thermometer), stirring occasionally; remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until candy begins to lose its gloss and pecans are coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Cook until set.
Store in a tightly covered container up to 2 weeks.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.

title: taco salsa
directions: Mince peppers (run through a grinder).
Cut up onion and tomatoes.
Mince garlic.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Boil about 1 hour.
Put in pint jar and water bath 10 minutes.

title: rave coconut cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Remove. When cool, fill and top with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: bacon salad dressing
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces; cook slowly until crisp.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour at once over lettuce, spinach or salad greens.

title: tomato and mozzarella salad
directions: On serving platter, arrange tomatoes, cheese and onions in overlapping layers.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over salad.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry delite
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Press in a 6 x 10-inch pan.
Beat until fluffy cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar, vanilla and whipping cream (whipped).
Pour over cracker crumb mixture and top with cherry pie filling.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cream milk and chocolate over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook and gently stir to 236°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and let cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick and not glossy.
Add 1 cup of broken nuts, if desired.
Spread in buttered pan.
Chill and cut into pieces.

title: coconut rum balls
directions: Mix crumbs, coconut and nuts in a large bowl.
Add condensed milk and rum.
Mix well and chill for 4 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 8 dozen.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Drain corn and beans, mix well with other ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish.
Crush 1 sleeve Ritz crackers and spread on top.
1 stick of margarine dotted on top.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Stir in oleo and milk.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: canadian bacon
directions: Score fat on side of bacon.
Place bacon, scored side up, in 9 x 5-inch glass dish.
Insert cloves in top of bacon.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over top.
Microwave for 10 minutes on Medium-high (roast).
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over top.
Microwave for 10 to 20 minutes on Medium-high (roast) or until meat is heated through (about 120°).
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: couscous or white rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and toss with the following salad dressing.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook until red disappears.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup. Simmer 10 minutes uncovered.
Skim off any grease.
Dollop on 1 cup sour cream just before serving over noodles or rice.

title: pecan swirl cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip each piece into melted butter, roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Pack into Bundt pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool in pan for about 5 minutes, then pour onto cake plate.

title: shoe bottom cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Cream well.
Add flour and a pinch of salt until you have a stiff dough.
Spread on a long cookie sheet.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Spread over dough.
On top, sprinkle 1 cup crushed pecans and pat down with hands.
Sprinkle just a little bit of sugar on top.
Bake at 250° until light brown.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: On a large plate, open can of refried beans.
Spread on plate. Add taco sauce, sour cream, avocados and grated cheese to the top.
Then add diced green onions and sliced olives.
Serve with corn chips.
Preparation time is 20 minutes.

title: crab casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and butter while still hot.
Place in greased casserole.
Mix in bowl #1 the egg, onion, cream cheese, salt, pepper, cottage cheese and basil.
Mix in bowl #2 the soup and crab meat.
Place 1/2 of mixture in bowl #1 on top of noodles in casserole.
Place all of bowl #2 over.
Place remaining contents of bowl #1 over that.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove and cool or freeze at this point.
If not frozen, use a topping of grated cheese and a few slices of tomato and bake another 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients in a separate bowl.
Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and vanilla gradually.
Add this to dry ingredients. Slowly stir in zucchini.
Mix 1 teaspoon flour and nuts.
Add zucchini and nuts to other mixture.
Grease and flour loaf or cake pan (tube).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then 10 minutes on rack.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: steak bake
directions: Place meat in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Toss to coat meat.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper, tomatoes, mushrooms, molasses and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir in beans.
Drop Tangy Muffins by tablespoon onto hot mixture.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for additional 15 to 18 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: easy pigs in a blanket
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and cut up cabbage in quarters.
Add soup and rice.
Cook on medium heat 30 minutes.
Season to taste. Serve with rolls and salad.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water, stirring well to dissolve completely.
Add cranberry sauce, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in pineapple.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate to set.

title: fruit buttermilk salad
directions: Combine jello and fruit cocktail in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cool slightly. Stir in buttermilk. Fold in topping.
Pour into large oblong dish. Sprinkle pecans over top. Chill well.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Season, brown and drain hamburger.
Drain green beans. Combine hamburger, green beans and tomato soup.
Place in round casserole dish.
Prepare 4 servings of instant mashed potatoes according to directions.
Place on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: huquenot torte
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly oil a 9-inch or 10-inch pan.
Beat eggs at high speed until thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes. Gradually beat in sugar until very thick.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat just until mixture is combined.
Fold in vanilla, apples, pecans and lemon juice.
Turn into dish.
Bake until top is crusty and brown, 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
Top with pecan halves if desired.

title: hamburger-pasta cheese bake
directions: Saute meat, onion and green pepper.
Add tomato sauce, sugar and seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Boil shells 4 minutes.
Drain on towels.
Fill shells with cottage cheese and grated cheese. Place in baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef 'n cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large frypan, combine ground beef, onion and green peppers.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans, garlic salt and salt.
Brown well.

title: spaghetti with red clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil until wilted.
Add juice from clams, tomato sauce, wine, basil and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add clams and cook 1 minute longer. Stir in parsley.
Toss sauce with hot pasta and serve with Parmesan cheese.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients at once and beat for 1 minute. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, 1/2 cup of sugar and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: "quick and easy" chicken teriyaki(serves 4)
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Spray a nonstick pan with Pam.
Brown chicken on both sides (about 6 minutes on each side).
Mix teriyaki sauce blend.
Pour over chicken; cook on low until chicken is tender.

title: granola
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add honey and oil.
Bake at 350° on flat sheet pan 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes while cooking. When baked, add dried apricots and raisins.
Put in bowl to cool, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit compote
directions: Put milk and juice in bowl.
Add pudding, then beat.
Add Cool Whip; beat altogether.
Drain all fruit well.
Mix all fruit together.
You may use different fruit if desired, other than strawberries.
In a deep bowl, add layer of fruit, then layer of pudding, layer of fruit and pudding again.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter freezer pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and peanut butter until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour this into a prepared graham cracker crust; top with ground peanuts.
Place in freezer.

title: choc-a-lot
directions: Mix all together.
Mix 1/4 cup of mix to a cup of hot milk or water.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix together. Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: pre-cruise cold veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls onto ungreased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rocky road frosting
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk and vanilla in bowl.
Add egg; beat until well blended.
Add chocolate; mix well.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Makes enough frosting for 2 layers.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and mash.
Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Stir in sugar, salt and flour.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Stir in carrots.
Spoon into oiled casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs, mix lightly.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish, sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown meat and add seasoning.
Melt cheese on top.
Place on cocktail rye bread and place on cookie sheet to freeze for at least 1 hour.
Put in plastic bags.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Stir eggs with a spoon in bowl.
Add sugar mixed with cocoa. Stir until well mixed.
Add melted butter, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, milk and salt together in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, then turn heat back to medium high for 10 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; mix.
If mixture is not thick enough, use extra peanut butter.
Pour onto buttered dinner plate.
Allow to cool.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Brown onions in oil and add beef.
Cook until the red is gone. Add tomatoes, corn, salt and pepper.
Mix 3/4 cup self-rising corn meal and 1/2 cup milk.
Spoon over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° until corn bread is browned.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Bring medium pot of salted water to a boil and blanch broccoli for 1 minute. Remove from water and place in ice water to stop cooking; strain and set aside. Repeat procedure with cauliflower and carrots. Carrots should be cooked last and cook for 2 minutes. Cook pasta. Heat 6 tablespoons of oil in large skillet; add small amount of garlic, red and green pepper, zucchini and squash and cook until slightly brown.	Remove from skillet and set aside. Add remainder of garlic and oil, broccoli, cauliflower and carrots and cook approximately 2 to 3 minutes. Return zucchini mixture to skillet and basil. Stir until mixed. Slowly add cream and cook until cream begins to boil. Remove from heat; place pasta in bowl and mix in vegetables and 3/4 of cheese. Use remaining cheese to garnish servings.

title: party smokies
directions: Cover wieners with water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, drain water.
In mixing bowl mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over wieners in saucepan, bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: double-apple walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 12-cup bundt pan. Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
At high speed beat butter until smooth.
Beat in sugar until fluffy.
Reduce speed to low.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Alternately beat in flour and applesauce; beat 1 minute.
Fold in apples.
Spread in pan.
Bake 1 hour, 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool on rack 40 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.

title: easy mexican dish
directions: Line dish with corn chips.
Brown hamburger meat; drain grease off and add other ingredients, except cheese.
Pour mixture over chips and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes a very large casserole, a whopper.

title: hot cheese biscuits
directions: Have butter and cheese room temperature.
Chill slightly. Shape into roll, chill again; slice thinly.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet; flatten.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
These freeze nicely, cooked or uncooked.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese, pineapple, onion, green pepper,
and seasoned salt.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Place crumb mixture in a well-greased deep cake pan.
Using back of a large spoon, press crumb mixture against bottom and sides to form a shell.
Force cottage cheese through a strainer.
Beat eggs; add cheese, remaining sugar, flour, milk, lemon juice and nutmeg.
Stir until well blended. Turn mixture into the shell and bake in a slow oven at 325°
for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let cake cool in pan.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Ready to use on lettuce, etc.

title: cake style cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add other ingredients and stir until just mixed.
Cook in 9 x 13-inch pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be made in cupcake pans using liners.
Makes 24.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and stuffing.
Place half into bottom of long casserole dish.
Boil zucchini until tender. Drain well.
Mix zucchini with onion, soup, sour cream and carrot. Put this mixture in pan.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together well.
Refrigerate.
Let set several hours before serving.
Serve with raw cauliflower, mushrooms, broccoli, celery and green peppers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water and then add pineapple juice.
Mash up cranberry sauce and mix in jello mixture and put in refrigerator and let thicken.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Put back in refrigerator.

title: cake of many flavors
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Grease and lightly flour a tube or Bundt pan. Cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add liqueur, vanilla, lemon and almond extracts and butter flavoring. Mix well. Combine all-purpose and self-rising flour and stir to mix. Add to batter alternately with the sour cream, beating until well blended. Pour into prepared pan and bake for about 1 hour 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake. Turn out of pan immediately. Allow to cool slightly before slicing.

title: bay scallops
directions: Sprinkle scallops with salt.
Melt butter in skillet with garlic.
Saute scallops on medium for about 10 minutes or opaque. Pour off juice from scallops.
Add wine, heavy cream and sour cream.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Simmer for 8 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs with a fork.
Mix in sugar and cinnamon, then milk. Dip bread, one slice at a time, in this mixture and fry in small amount of oil on medium heat.
Turn and brown on other side. Serve with syrup.
(This is not for serious dieters!)

title: chocolate crunch
directions: Layer Saltines on foil on a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Boil margarine and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes. Remove and sprinkle with chips.
Spread melting chocolate, returning pan to oven for 1 to 2 minutes, if necessary to melt all chocolate for spreading.
Refrigerate until chilled. Break into pieces.

title: shell macaroni-artichoke salad
directions: Cook shell macaroni.
Add artichokes, green pepper, pimento, olives and onions.
Coat with dressing (to taste).
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor results.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet-sour sauce
directions: Combine 3/4 cup water, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and salt. Heat to boiling.
Blend together cornstarch and water until smooth.
Slowly stir into boiling mixture.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.

title: cheese log
directions: Cream together with fork; shape and fold in chopped nuts and dried parsley flakes (sprinkled over wax paper).
Coat the cheese log thoroughly with this mixture.
Refrigerate wrapped in wax paper until serving time.

title: baked yams tahiti
directions: Drain yams and pineapple; mash together with bananas.
Add sherry, salt and pepper; whip until smooth.
Place mixture in buttered casserole.
Dot with butter and marshmallows.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until it bubbles slightly and the marshmallows turn brown.

title: mimi's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease and flour 8 x 12-inch pan.
Melt in double boiler the butter and chocolate.
Add sugar, egg, vanilla, flour and 1 teaspoon baking powder and all the pecans you wish.
Mix lightly and pour in pan.
Bake at 275° until toothpick comes out clean.
This makes a chewy brownie.

title: cinnamon frosted raisin bars
directions: In saucepan, combine the granulated sugar and cornstarch. Stir in water and raisins.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and clear.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix meat, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Add enough ketchup to make mixture stick.
Make into balls the size of walnuts.
Place in baking dish and pour tomato sauce over meat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chow fun
directions: Cook noodles in hot, salty water.
While noodles are cooking (don't overcook), mix the ginger, sugar, salt and soyu.
Set aside.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Place a layer of asparagus, sliced eggs, almonds and mushroom soup.
Repeat.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Heat for 45 minutes in 325° oven or until bubbly.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook meats; drain.
Add tomatoes.
Stir in seasonings.
Heat to boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: diet peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs and margarine together and press into 9-inch pie pan.
