Bake until brown, let cool.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix ingredients well and then place in refrigerator to chill about 1 hour.
Then roll in small balls and place back in refrigerator a little longer.

title: the ruby slipper
directions: Mix 2 minutes.
Put into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add unbeaten eggs and butter. Stir well.
Add vanilla and apples.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken-macaroni casserole\(serves 6)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: florentine lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Cool in large bowl of ice water; set aside. Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter 5 minutes.
Combine spinach, onion, Mozzarella cheese, sour cream and 1 egg.
Set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, instant bouillon and pepper.
Stir in milk and cream.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.

title: poppy cheese loaf
directions: Mix biscuit mix, cheese, seeds, onions and garlic salt.
Add egg and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350 degrees about 1 hour.

title: favorite broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix last 3 ingredients until smooth.
Pour dressing over salad and toss. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mrs. dave long's appetizers
directions: Wrap bacon around each piece of water chestnut and secure with toothpick.
Place in baking pan.
Mix chili sauce, mayonnaise and brown sugar.
Pour on top of water chestnuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Work flour, sugar and oleo together as for pie dough.
Coarse crumbs, put aside 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
Mix molasses, boiling water and soda.
Combine with remaining crumbs and mix well by hand. Batter will be thin.
Cool mixture.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle the 1 1/2 cups crumbs over the cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown beef; cook slowly for 4 hours.
Separate meat with fork. Remove any fat or bones.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer. Serve on hamburger buns.
This will freeze very well.

title: sweet pickled watermelon rind
directions: Cover cubed rind with salt and water; let set overnight. Rinse, drain, cover with fresh water and simmer slowly until tender.
Drain.
Combine cloves, spices, cinnamon and lemon slices in cheesecloth bag.
Add spice bag to vinegar, water and sugar in saucepan.
Add melon and simmer until transparent.
Seal in jars. Can be frozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: a-1 best cheesecake
directions: Mix nuts, butter, sprinkle of cinnamon and sprinkle of Splenda together and press into bottom of 9-inch deep-dish pie plate.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, heavy cream, vanilla, Splenda and eggs to make filling.
Blend until very smooth.
Pour in pie plate.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set (in water bath) pan with 1-inch or so of water.
Chill for 2 hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit, saving all
juices
from fruit except from apple rings (can use
small
amount for color).
Arrange fruit in alternate layers in a
9 x 13-inch casserole dish.	Combine sugar, flour, margarine, juice and cooking sherry in saucepan. Cook, stirring until smooth
and	thickened.
Pour
over fruit and cover.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Heat oven at 350°. Cook until hot
and
bubbly (approximately 25 minutes). Excellent with pork or poultry.

title: ann's chicken divan
directions: Boil, bone and cube chicken.
Steam broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, curry powder and soup in large casserole dish. Place layers of broccoli, chicken and soup mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Place in oven until hot and bubbly and cheese is melted.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bible cake
directions: Bake at 350° in layers 25 to 30 minutes.
Loaf or Bundt pan for 1 hour.
Serve plain or frosted.

title: texas gold bars
directions: Combine the cake mix, 1 egg and oleo and mix well.
Pat into a 12 x 9 x 1-inch pan.

title: old fashioned jelly roll
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Combine baking powder, salt and eggs in bowl.
Place over smaller bowl of hot water and beat with mixer, adding sugar gradually until mixture becomes thick and light colored.
Remove bowl from hot water.
Fold in flour and vanilla.
Turn into greased, wax paper lined pan (15 x 10-inch) and bake in hot oven (400°) for 13 minutes.
Quickly cut off crisp edges of cake.
Turn from pan at once onto cloth covered with powdered sugar.
Remove paper.
Spread jelly, spreading almost to edge.
Roll quickly and wrap in cloth.
Let cool.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Use juice from pineapple and add enough water to make 2 cups. Boil water and dissolve Jell-O.
Add pineapple, pie filling and nuts.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Cut flowers into bite-sized pieces.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over broccoli.
Refrigerate tightly covered for 24 hours, shaking several times.
As broccoli is used, more can be added; also cauliflower and carrots can be used.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Once the tomatoes are peeled, cut them into wedges and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, saute the onions and bell pepper in the butter briefly, until slightly soft.
Add the honey and tomato wedges; cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: chinese chewies
directions: In deep mixing bowl, blend in dark brown sugar and margarine until smooth.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Gradually add in flour, mixing until well blended.
Add pecans and mix well.
Have oven preheated to 350° (ovens vary in cooking).

title: taco dip(appetizer)
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add spices.
Spread on serving platter.
Layer chopped onion, green pepper, shredded cheese, shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes.
Serve with Doritos.

title: squash pie with nuts
directions: Mix well and bake in 8 to 9-inch pie crust at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 45 minutes longer or until a knife blade comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold.
May be topped with a dollop of whipped cream or Cool Whip when served.

title: old-fashioned rhubarb cake
directions: In a bowl, cream the butter and 1 cup of sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla in a separate bowl.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk-vanilla to creamed mixture.
Stir in fruit.
Spread in greased baking pan.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: eggless devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure, add sugar, cocoa, soda and baking powder; sift together 2 or 3 times.
Cream butter and milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Flavor and bake in moderate oven.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter until limp, add these to eggs, well beaten with sour cream.
Add several shakes of Tabasco and salt and pepper.
Mix all well and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Top heavily with Parmesan cheese and bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine the salad dressing, soup, egg, onion, green pepper, lemon juice and salt; mix well.
Add the salmon and bread crumbs; toss lightly.
Place in a well-greased 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Unmold and surround with endive.
Garnish with lemon wedges and cucumber twists.

title: tender-juicy ham
directions: Wrap ham in heavy duty Reynolds wrap.
Pour can of Coke over. Wrap up tightly with Reynolds wrap.
Let cook 10 hours in 200° oven.
Put on at night and next morning it's ready for the day.

title: vegetable surprise
directions: Melt cheese, then add margarine and melt.
Mix with vegetables; place in flat casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: little league stew
directions: Peel potatoes, carrots and onion.
Cut into bite size pieces. Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.
Cover and bake 4 hours at 300°.

title: peppered beef salad
directions: Trim fat from beef.
For salad dressing and marinade, in a screwtop jar combine the vinegar, sugar, pepper, dry mustard, oregano, garlic, 1 cup water and dash of salt.
Cover; shake well to combine.
Place meat in a shallow 2-quart dish.
Pour about half of the vinegar mixture over the meat (about 2/3 cup).
Turn meat to coat with the marinade.
Cover meat; marinate in the refrigerator for 6 to 24 hours, turning occasionally.
To the remaining vinegar mixture, add the powdered fruit pectin.
Cover and shake well to combine.
Let mixture stand several minutes and shake again.
Chill dressing until serving time.

title: quick chili
directions: Add all ingredients to a large crock-pot and cook on low all day.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by large teaspoonfuls on nonstick cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion and sherry.
Layer spaghetti and turkey in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture on top.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Top with buttered mushrooms. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: fresh raspberry kuchen
directions: If using frozen raspberries, thaw at room temperature for 15 minutes. Drain. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: grandma best sugar cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift flour and soda into sugar mixture.
Roll out into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press out with sugar dipped glass bottom.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Cream melted butter and sugar and flour.
Add eggs; the milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 1 hour at 325 degrees.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix molasses, sugar and sour milk.
Add melted shortening. Add sifted flour and dry ingredients.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Roll. Cut.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 375°.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Brown bottom pie crust.
Put all mixed ingredients in shell.
Place dabs of butter on peaches. Close with crust.
Foil edges.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: buffalo bisque cheese pie
directions: Chill milk in freezing tray until frozen about 1/2 inch around pan.
Dissolve jello in boiling water, then add softened Knox gelatine to it.
Add sugar, salt, lemon juice and lemon rind when jello has congealed slightly.
Add slowly to softened cream cheese and milk which has been whipped stiff.
Continue whipping until well blended.
Add pineapple, cherries and nuts.

title: rum balls
directions: Grind or roll wafers very fine.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add nuts, syrup and rum.
Stir until stiff.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Coat hands with powdered sugar when shaping balls. Let stand for one hour to partially dry out.
Roll in powdered sugar.
These may be stored in a tin container or cookie jar and will keep well for several weeks.
No cooking is required.
Makes about 40 balls.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring large saucepan of water to boil.
Add vegetables and boil 1 minute.
Drain.
Place in large bowl.
Add olives.
In small bowl, combine next ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables; stir to coat.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes. (Good overnight even.)

title: shrimp alfredo sauce
directions: Melt all of this in saucepan.
Cook slowly until thick and creamy.
Add 1/2 cup sauteed shrimp.
You may add asparagus or mushrooms, if desired.
Serve on buttered fettucini noodles.

title: chicken kabobs(serves 1)
directions: Simmer chicken cubes, mushrooms and green peppers in chicken soup for 15 minutes; season with pepper, ginger and garlic powder. Place chicken cubes, mushrooms and green peppers on toothpicks and serve.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Crumble crackers on the bottom.
Add a layer of oysters.
Cut celery very fine and sprinkle over. Sprinkle parsley flakes; dot with butter.
Add a little oyster liquid if fresh oysters are used.
Don't add oyster liquid if canned oysters are used.
Pour over casserole.
Take fork and pat down until milk oozes on top.
Cook for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Beat together eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Add to dry mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 25 to 30 servings.

title: zesty french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in bottle or jar.
Cover tightly and shake well.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake before serving.
Yields 2 cups.

title: chuck roast oregano
directions: Mix salt, pepper and vinegar and add to meat.
You can do this day before baking roast.
Brown meat in 400° oven in large roast pan for 20 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° or 325°.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce to chopped onion.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Cook vermicelli when meat is cooked.
Add vermicelli and serve with a salad.
Enjoy!

title: shrimp stroganoff
directions: Saute onion butter.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Add flour, seasonings and remaining ingredients, except sour cream. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sour cream before serving.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt; mix with apples.
Turn into ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches. Dot with butter.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Remove crust from bread and break up.
Melt margarine and pour over bread crumbs.
Place mustard, salt, pepper, egg yolks, milk, cheese and bread crumbs together and mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into egg mixture.
Pour into buttered baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Cook the cauliflower until almost tender.
Beat the egg, salt and water together until blended.
Dip flowerets into egg, then crumbs until coated and set aside to dry.
Heat fat to 190°C. Slip breaded flowerets into hot fat, a few at a time, and cook until lightly browned.
Remove from fat; drain on absorbent paper.
Serve.
Strain fat after it cools.
Try different vegetables for a variety of flavors.

title: salsa sauce hors d'oeuvre
directions: We use a manual food grinder with coarse blade for all dicing. Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place in 3-quart saucepan on medium heat, stir frequently.
Add cornstarch and bring to low boil.
Take off from heat.
Let cool before putting in containers.
The longer it sets the better it gets.
Serve with chips.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed 15 seconds or until mixed together.
Pour into pie plate and bake 1 hour.

title: daisy keats' cheese croquettes
directions: Mix well by hand.
Mold into 6 or 8 croquettes.
Roll in egg whites combined with condensed milk.
Roll in flour, then repeat process second time.
Set aside in refrigerator until croquettes get firm.
Drop one croquette at a time in hot oil in skillet. Roll over until brown, a process that should take less than a minute.
Drain on paper towels.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and drained fruit cocktail.
Add Eagle Brand milk and stir.
Add lemon juice.
You can add nuts, cherries, pineapple or coconut.

title: chinese green salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and ginger root in small bowl.
Cover; let stand 30 minutes.
Combine the next 4 ingredients; toss gently.
Pour salad dressing over salad; toss gently.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vinegar dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Cool.
Can be made ahead and stored in jar in refrigerator; ready when needed.

title: brunch
directions: Spread bread with butter.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish
and
set aside.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spread over bread slices.
Sprinkle	cheese	over
sausage.	Combine remainder of ingredients
and
mix
well; pour over bread and sausage.
Cover and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake
at
for
45 minutes or until set.
Great for Christmas or New Year's morning!

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup for 4 minutes.
Add salted nuts and cook 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and margarine; cook 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and mix fast.
Pour immediately onto buttered pan.

title: mrs. stover's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and oleo; stir well before cooking.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; fold in 3 packages chocolate chips and marshmallow whip.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered pans.
Top with nuts.

title: chicken divan
directions: Drain chicken and debone.
Cook rice in broth.
Place broccoli in Pyrex dish, then rice and chicken.
Top with sauce and croutons.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, cinnamon and eggs.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top this with yellow cake mix (sprinkle, do not mix).
Sprinkle pecans on top of cake mix.
Cover nuts with pieces of butter.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Let cool completely.
Beat whipping cream, cream cheese and powdered sugar together and spread on top of cooled pie.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Combine seasonings in bowl.
Place 2 tablespoons melted margarine in 10-inch skillet.
Arrange 1/3 potatoes in circular pattern.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon seasoning, 4 tablespoons melted margarine and 2 tablespoons onion.
Repeat layers twice. Cover tightly with foil.
Press down.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°. Remove foil.
Cook 20 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before putting in serving dish.

title: pickled beans
directions: Cook beans in boiling salted water until tender.
Use 1 teaspoon salt to each quart of water.
Drain and pack in hot syrup.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over beans and seal.
Makes 8 quarts.
Cut the ends off the beans and leave beans uncut.

title: codfish cakes
directions: Soak codfish in water overnight.
Drain off water and place codfish and peeled potatoes in cold water to cook together for 1/2 hour.
Mash potatoes.
Shred codfish.
Then mix the two together. Add egg, onion, pepper and parsley.
Form into cakes; fry on both sides until brown.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes by hand.
Take out seeds and core.
Cut tomatoes in fine pieces.
Chop onions fine.
Put sugar over tomatoes.
Chop peppers fine and add to tomatoes.
Cook 1 hour.

title: lentil delight
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper over low heat.
Add lentils and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, stirring frequently, until lentils are fully tender.
Serve with rice (try brown rice) or as a side dish.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 4 hours.

title: cuban chicken fricassee
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, brown the chicken in the olive oil.
When all the chicken parts are well browned, add the chopped onions, bell pepper and garlic and cook until the onions and peppers are tender.
Then add the oregano, cumin, wine, tomato sauce, salt and pepper and stir.
Add the carrots, potatoes, olives and raisins and when it starts to boil, cover the pot, turn the heat down and cook it approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until the chicken is tender.
If it needs more liquid, add water as necessary.
Ten minutes before serving, sprinkle the peas on top. Serve it with steamed white rice and a fresh green salad.

title: banana float
directions: Blend at low speed.

title: fairy tale's
directions: Mix well and cook for 45 minutes and chew well. So that should fell you up.

title: raisin-spice cupcakes
directions: Boil raisins and water together for 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain raisins and save juice/water.
Add warm water to raisin liquid if needed to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Add to liquid the soda.
Cream the next 6 ingredients together.
Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Combine flour and baking powder in separate bowl.
Add flour and baking powder to creamed mixture alternately with raisin water.
Mix well.
Add the drained raisins to batter.
Put mixture in muffin pans using cupcake liners (for better storage) to 1/2 or 1/3 full.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar on each cupcake before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
These freeze well.
Warm in microwave, if desired.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix and pour into baking pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, onion, sour cream, hot taco sauce and chilies.
Spread over tortillas.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap in a damp paper towel.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mixed veggie casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix celery, onion, mayonnaise, shredded cheese and bread crumbs.
Spoon this mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine 2 tablespoons margarine with crackers; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 300° until bubbly.

title: mexican pizza dip
directions: Take a flat pan or a glass serving plate and start building your dip.
Start with the bean dip and spread it over the plate. Next, pour the taco seasoned sour cream over the bean dip.
Work your way down the list of ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips or strips (preferably unsalted).

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwaveable bowl at High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and 1 cup nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Immediately sprinkle marshmallows, chips and remaining nuts over brownies.
Return to oven and bake for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover warm dish until cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 24 servings.

title: congo squares
directions: In a saucepan, melt shortening over medium heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Cool slightly; combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually with eggs to shortening mixture.
Stir in vanilla, chips and nuts (batter will be very stiff).
Spread into a greased and floured 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Yield:
48 bars.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Put drained asparagus into buttered baking dish.
Chop egg and put layer over asparagus, then a layer grated cheese.
Add a layer drained peas.
Dot with butter and season with salt and pepper. Pour soup on top and top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add Crisco, vanilla and half of milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add rest of milk and eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Mix walnuts into batter. Bake in 2 nine-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash and whip bananas very lightly.
In another bowl, cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda and nuts alternately with bananas.
Add pineapple and pudding mix.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 65 minutes or until done.

title: sand cookies
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and baking soda for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough on cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: italian tuna melt
directions: Separate crescent rolls; flatten slightly.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Stir together 1/3 cup tomato paste and 2 tablespoons of the mayonnaise.
Spread 1 tablespoon paste mixture on each roll.

title: microwave goulash
directions: Cook onion and butter for 2 minutes.
Add ground beef and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and macaroni and cook another 4 to 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Add to casserole and cook 1 more minute.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Combine rice, blueberries and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Coat 8 individual custard cups or 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place rice mixture in bottom.
In another bowl, combine bran, flour, walnuts, remaining 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Mix in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over rice mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: super simple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil 9 x 13-inch pan with the 1/4 cup of oil.
Add cake mix, cherry pie filling, eggs and water.
Stir for about 2 minutes, until mix is moistened.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: you're lucky if any is left
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip. Mix pineapple, cornstarch and lemon juice; cook unti thick.
Set aside until cool.
Layer graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not crush the crackers.
Put a layer of crackers and a layer of filling.
Repeat until all are used up.
Top with pineapple filling.
Put in refrigerator overnight or until it sets.
Will slice beautiful if cold.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt butter and add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add corn, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg yolks.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and add mushrooms. Fold in the beaten egg whites and pour in buttered baking dish. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 300° to 350°.
Garnish with parsley and with bacon, cut in small pieces and fried crisp.

title: chicken and pasta casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
In medium bowl, stir soup, mustard, oregano, pepper and milk until smooth.
Spoon 1 cup soup mixture over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
In large bowl, combine pasta and vegetables, 1/2 can onions and remaining soup mixture.
Spoon pasta mixture under and around chicken.
Bake an additional 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and sauce is bubbling.
Top with tomato wedges and remaining onions.
Bake 3 minutes.

title: texas salad
directions: Cook sirloin steak on grill to desired doneness.
Slice into 1/4 inch strips.
Place in 8 x 11.5 x 2 inch pan.
Add green pepper, tomatoes and onions.
Mix vinegar, salad oil and garlic and pour over meat and vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: mexicali bean spread
directions: In a food processor or blender, whirl the kidney beans, water, tomato paste, lemon juice, cumin, oregano, red pepper sauce and cinnamon for 1 minute or until smooth.

title: homestyle meat loaf
directions: Combine 1/4 cup gravy with beef and add bread crumbs, chopped onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into loaf in baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat remaining gravy; serve over meat loaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: party franks
directions: Combine gravy and water, stirring with a wire whip over low heat.
Stir in honey, catsup and mustard, cooking 2 minutes over low heat.
Add wieners and cook over low heat until they are hot. Keep warm while serving.
Serve with picks.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the sugar and milk in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until the mixture comes to a full boil.
Let boil for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Put mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan and allow to cool.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Add ingredients, 1 at a time (in bowl or blender), beating well after each addition. Pour into unbaked deep-dish pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix lettuce, apples and walnuts together.
Pour all other ingredients over salad and toss.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vinegar and food coloring and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and continue baking for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: mama's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, sugar and salt.
Add small amount of milk to dampen well.
Add remaining milk and stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla. Great for breakfast over hot buttered biscuits.

title: gram's coffee cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, soda and powder to mixture alternately with sour cream.

title: festive fruit compote
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; set aside.
Combine brown sugar and remaining ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over fruit mixture and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add pineapple juice. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: pecan cookies(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding mix. Add oil, egg and vanilla. Add chopped pecans. Roll into small balls. Bake at 325° until brown.

title: granny's blueberry muffins
directions: Sprinkle berries with 1/2 teaspoon flour; set aside.
Sift dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Add milk and beaten egg.
Fold in floured berries quickly; be careful not to mash them.
Bake in hot greased muffin pans for 20 minutes at 350° or until done. Yield:
12 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated wild turkey
directions: You will need green hickory wood.

title: gina's italian pasta
directions: Slow simmer sauce, tomatoes and black olives.
Season to taste. Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Rinse pasta with hot water and drain well.
Toss pasta together with tomato mixture. Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a shallow 2-quart baking dish, combine apples, water and lemon juice.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in walnuts and oats. Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm or at room temperature with ice cream or whipping cream, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with sauce before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
The longer it stands, the better it gets.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and add pickles, onion, catsup and Tabasco sauce.
Heat through.
Makes enough for two pounds of hot dogs.

title: lima beans with ham bone
directions: Wash lima beans thoroughly; discard discolored, spoiled beans. Add beans to water and ham bone.
Cook, adding water as necessary.
When beans are completely soft, cook down to a thick, soupy consistency.
Cut chunks of ham from bone and cook in beans. Garnish with diced raw onions, if desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: oriental brown rice
directions: Place 1 tablespoon oil in a skillet and heat.
Add raw brown rice slowly, stirring continuously, until each grain is coated with oil.
Pour water into a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add oil-coated rice slowly and cover pot.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Stir-fry mushrooms in 1 tablespoon of sesame oil; set aside.
Add remainder of oil to skillet and stir-fry remaining vegetables and garlic.
Add cooked mushrooms and rice.
Add tamari.
Quickly scramble the two eggs and break apart; add to mixture.
Toss all lightly and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients, except whipped topping and cinnamon, until blended.
Spoon into two dessert dishes.
Cover and refrigerate or serve immediately.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Place in large shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle on top. Chill several hours or overnight.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until heated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: maureen's french silk pie
directions: Cream butter in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, creaming with butter. Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating rapidly for 5 minutes after each egg is added.
Fold into pie shell.
Chill several hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Add while hot, cream cheese, 1/4 stick margarine and soup.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Cook onion in 3/4 stick margarine until tender.
Pick out the onion and add to the broccoli.
Save butter drippings and add to cracker crumbs. Place cracker crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: dilly green tomatoes
directions: Pack tomatoes in Mason jars.
Add first 4 ingredients (dill, garlic, celery and pepper) to each jar.
Cook water, vinegar and salt for 5 minutes.
Fill jars half-full and seal.
Makes about 8 quart jars.

title: easy tarts
directions: Put a wafer in each of the cupcake papers. Dab each with butter.
Mix next 5 ingredients spooning cup 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Place 1 Tbsp. pie filling on each.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and Crisco.
When Crisco is melted, mixture is lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast in 3/4 cup warm water. Add egg to mixture.
Add cornmeal and mix well.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured board, adding flour and kneading until can hold dough in palm of hand.
Put in bowl. Cover until double in bulk.
Make into rolls and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: six-week muffin mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl; cover and store in refrigerator.
When ready for muffins, fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Store rest of batter in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks, using as needed.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased lightly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole.
Crumble chow mein noodles on top.
Add a little chicken broth for moisture.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Mix crab meat, along with onions, green pepper and pickles until it's equally distributed.
Add Tabasco sauce and 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle seafood seasoning to your discretion.
Serve on lettuce with crackers.
Can add Worcestershire sauce (optional).
Serves 4.

title: guava fruit punch
directions: Combine juices, sugar and grenadine in 2 1/2-quart container. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Pour over ice ring in punch bowl.
Garnish with fresh fruit. Makes 18 (4 ounce) punch size cups.

title: quick tuna and noodles
directions: Cook noodles
as
directed.
Pour off water and stir in butter.
Add tuna (with oil if not dieting), mushroom soup and milk to
noodles.
Stir
until mixed well.	Put back on medium heat, stirring
often until heated through.
Lay cheese on top of mixture;
put top on pan and heat again until cheese melts.

title: cheesy ham sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix
ham, cheese, mayonnaise and onion. Place 1/3 cup of
mixture on each bun.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake 15 to
minutes or until hot and cheese begins to melt.
Serves 8.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats in boiling water until cool.
Cream butter and eggs; add to oatmeal mixture.
Sift cinnamon, soda, eggs and salt and add to the other mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Cut into lengthwise strips.
In skillet, stir brown sugar, salt and butter until bubbly.
Add carrots; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, 5 to 10 minutes or until carrots are glazed and heated thoroughly.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put into greased casserole.
Bake in slow oven at 300°, uncovered, for 1 hour or until set and browned.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Cook pork sausage until redness is gone.
Combine all ingredients and bake in casserole dish until tender for 1 1/2 hours, stirring once.
If liquid is needed, add chicken broth.

title: pineapple-carrot bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add beaten eggs, oil, grated carrots, pineapple, vanilla and nuts. Place in 2 large greased loaf pans or 1 large and 2 small loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet; sprinkle with sugar on top with 1/2 pecan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, milk and flour together.
Melt butter in baking pan and pour flour mixture on butter; add fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chow chow
directions: Wash vegetables.
Using a coarse blade, grind them up. Sprinkle with pickling salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Bring to a boil all other ingredients and boil 5 minutes. Fill jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes. Makes 9 pints.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Heat cheese and soup together.
After chicken has boiled to tenderness, debone.
Layer in casserole dish the chicken, salt and pepper to taste, broccoli, cheese and soup mixture.
Crush Ritz crackers and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding and Tang with pineapple and juice.
Add fruit and mix well.

title: dorothy's gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and stir.
Thoroughly stir in dry ingredients, then nuts and gumdrops.
Line cookie sheet with foil; spray with vegetable spray.
Drop walnut size chunks of dough on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 8 slices of bread.
Cover with ham and cheese; add a layer of 8 more slices of bread.
Mix together in bowl, the eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour this over the bread layer.
Set in refrigerator for 5 hours.
Mix 1 cup cornflakes with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and tomato fettuccine
directions: Cook broccoli and stir broccoli in dressing.
Cook tomatoes in small saucepan over low heat 5 minutes.
Serve over fettuccine. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: green bean salad
directions: Cut tips off beans and slice 2-inches in length.
Cook beans in a small amount of lightly salted water in a covered saucepan for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Set aside to cool. Combine oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper separately and set aside.
Add cooled beans to oil mixture; mix well.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
Discard garlic before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In Dutch oven over medium heat in hot oil, cook beef until well browned.
Add water and next 9 ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Add beans (drained).
Add parsley.
Heat.
Pass Parmesan cheese.

title: string beans with a chinese flavor
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until tender-crisp.
Moisten cornstarch with a little cold water.
Add ginger, garlic salt and soy sauce.
Add 1/4 cup hot chicken stock and stir.
Return to hot vegetable.
Cook until thickened.
Season to taste.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Cook cake first.
Boil the pineapple juice and sugar together for 5 minutes. Pour over cake (9 x 13-inch pan) while still warm. Cool cake.
Add sliced bananas and pineapple to top of cake.
Fix pudding as directed.
Pour over bananas.
Put Cool Whip on next. Sprinkle with coconut and nuts if you like, then refrigerate.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: combine cake mix, apricot nectar, vegetable oil and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing will after each addition.
Pour into a greased bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
Cool right side up for 15 minutes; remove from pan, sift confectioners sugar and mix with lemon juice.
Pour over cake while still warm to make a glaze.

title: n a c penicillin chicken soup(serves 6 to 10 people)
directions: Put whole chicken, cleaned, into large pot of water (1 to 2 gallons).
Add salt, garlic and onions.
Bring to boil and skim top prior and during boiling.
Add chopped carrots and celery. After chicken has boiled for 10 to 20 minutes, remove, skin and debone.
Dice chicken meat and put back in pot.
Bring back to a boil and add Italian seasonings and spinach.
Cook 2 to
5 minutes.

title: wild rice and mushroom soup
directions: Combine chicken broth and rice in small saucepan.
Cover and simmer over medium low heat until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 50 minutes.
Meanwhile, soak mushrooms in 1 1/2 cups hot water until soft, about 20 minutes.
Drain mushrooms, reserving soaking liquid.
Cut off mushroom stems and discard. Thinly slice mushrooms.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in heavy, large saucepan over medium high heat.
Add mushrooms; saute until tender and golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to small bowl.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in same pan.
Add onion, garlic, rosemary and thyme; saute until onion is very tender, about 10 minutes.
Mix in potato, beef stock and reserved mushroom soaking liquid.
Cover and simmer until potato is very tender, about 15 minutes.
Transfer soup to blender in batches; puree until smooth. Return to saucepan.
Stir in wild rice, mushrooms, 3/4 cup milk and Madeira.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes to blend flavors. Season with salt and pepper.
Thin with additional milk, if desired.

title: chocolate mousse in a minute(use with death by chocolate)
directions: Prepare pudding mix, using 1 1/2 cups milk. Fold in Cool Whip. You will need to double for this recipe (Death by Chocolate).

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased 13 x 16-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix soup with sour cream. Crush crackers. Add poppy seed and margarine. Make 2 layers, starting with chicken, then soup/sour cream mixture, then Ritz/poppy seed mixture.
Bake, uncovered, about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in lightly greased 10 x 13-inch pan on 300° for 50 minutes or lightly brown.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: Grease 8 or 9-inch square pan; dust well with flour.
Mix ingredients together and pour into floured pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon butter frosting
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, lemon peel and salt. Gradually add lemon juice.
If necessary, add a drop or two of water for right consistency. Top with coconut, if desired.

title: thieves steak sauce
directions: Mix together and heat for 15 minutes in microwave.
Can be frozen and/or made ahead to be stored in refrigerator.
May be served over hamburger patties, cooked.

title: carrots and cheese
directions: Slice and cook 2 pounds carrots.
Melt 1/3 stick oleo and 1 small carton Velveeta cheese.
Drain carrots and mix with butter and cheese.
Melt 2/3 stick oleo and put in 1/4 pound crackers. Brown the crackers for 15 minutes, then put on top of carrots. Heat in moderate oven.

title: chicago hot meat sauce
directions: Mix well.
Put in small jars and seal with paraffin.
Makes approximately 9 pints.

title: hill country casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, saute the garlic in the olive oil.
Add the meat to the skillet and brown.
Add salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine the cream cheese, sour cream and green onions.
Place the noodles in a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with cream cheese mixture and then the meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly (about 30 minutes).
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend first three ingredients and pour into crust. Chill before serving.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix Knox gelatine and 2 cups cold water together.
Set aside. Mix remaining ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Combine with first mixture and add 1 cup cold water.
Pour into large pan or 2 small ones and jell.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Combine condensed milk and water in large bowl. Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill about 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
(Make sure Cool Whip is not frozen because it will not mix easily if frozen.)

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix well and line 9 x 15-inch pan.
Save 3/4 cup crumbs for top.

title: sugarless fruit and nut muffins
directions: In saucepan, combine dates, raisins, prunes and water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Stir in margarine and salt.
Set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients to fruit.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into greased mini muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 32 muffins.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple; add water to make 2 cups. Heat juice to boiling. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved; cool. Add Cola and fruits to gelatin mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold or container. Chill until set.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs. Add all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a greased loaf pan.

title: spinach spread
directions: Squeeze water out of spinach.
Chop chestnuts and onion.
Mix together and add seasonings and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Spread on bread.

title: french bread
directions: Add 4 cups flour and mix thoroughly 10 minutes 1 teaspoon salt in 1 teaspoon water.
Let rise two times.
Put bottom in cornmeal-flour for top.
Slice after rises.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a medium bowl, toss apples with lemon juice. Stir in celery, nuts, raisins and grapes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together well and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with the following mixture and bake at 350° for 25 minutes:

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese until creamed.
Add confectioners sugar and mix.
Add half of the tub of Cool Whip and mix until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust and put the rest of Cool Whip on top of pie.
Freeze or refrigerate.
Fast, easy and good.

title: lo-cal crock-pot
directions: Add vegetables and meat to crock-pot.
Add V-8; season with oregano or Italian seasoning or your favorite spice combo.
Cook on slow/low crock-pot setting for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve in large soup bowls.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Delicious!
Makes about 200 calories per serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli into bite size pieces.
In large bowl, add broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon.
Toss.
In small bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour dressing over broccoli mixture and toss.
Refrigerate for one hour and toss before serving.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in water to cover until tender; cool, bone and cube.
Reserve 1 cup stock.
Combine chicken soup and milk. Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Melt margarine in stock and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in concentrate.
Combine cranberries, apple and sugar.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a 1 1/2 qt. serving dish.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Yields:
6 - 8 servings.

title: zucchini dills
directions: Slice zucchini into 8 pieces.
Put slits in peppers and leave whole.
Mix vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over zucchini and put in refrigerator.
Stir occasionally until desired hotness is obtained. Recipe good for cauliflower, carrots and small white onions, also.

title: company casserole(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook noodles until tender in boiling water, salted.
Drain, rinse with cold water.
Melt butter in skillet, add meat and cook and stir until meat has lost red color.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer gently 5 minutes.

title: home made vegetable soup
directions: Simmer all at least 30 minutes.
If you add macaroni add it now and cook for an additional 10 minutes.

title: almost pink champagne
directions: For a dramatic and easy-to-make ice bucket to hold bottles of wine, fresh flowers and water can be frozen into the shape of a bucket.

You will need a 4 or 5-quart container such as a plastic ice cream bucket, a 1-quart or 1 liter plastic bottle slightly larger than a wine bottle with the top 2 inches cut off and enough dried beans or marbles to fill the bottle, ice cubes and fresh flowers to match your party decor.

title: apple butter biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all liquid ingredients together. Add sugar, baking powder and flour.
Spread some flour on table or counter and roll dough flat.
Add more flour, if needed.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Take 1/2 cup of friendship.
Add a cup of thoughtfulness. Cream together with pinch of powdered togetherness.
Very lightly beaten in a bowl of loyalty.
With a cup of faith, one of hope and one of charity.
Be sure to add a spoonful of gaiety that sings and also the ability to laugh at little things.
Moisten with the sudden tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a good natured pan and serve repeatedly.

title: todd's "triples treats"
directions: Butter glass rectangular pan.
Place margarine and marshmallows in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring after 1 minute, until mixture is melted and smooth.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
Press mixture in pan using buttered back of spoon.
Cool.
Makes 16 to 24 bars.
Great treat for "snack Mom!"

title: grandma's meatball and potato dish
directions: Form the meat into extra large meatballs (about 6-inch). Brown well in heavy skillet.
Remove from pan.
Add cold water to the pan and scrape all the brown bits from the bottom of the pan while still very hot.
Turn heat to low and add as much water as needed for gravy to cover all meat, potatoes and onions.
Make your gravy with flour, salt, pepper and crushed gravy to taste.
Put meatballs back in skillet, cover with thinly sliced onions and peeled potatoes (cut in half).
cover completely with gravy. Cover and simmer 2 or 3 hours.
The longer, the better.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add egg.
Mix until batter is in fine crumbs.
Add fruit cocktail (drained).
Pour into greased round 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle gently on top brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: el paso venison
directions: Brown venison and chopped onion. Set aside.
In an 8 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish, layer all ingredients in the following order:
refried beans (spread to cover bottom of dish), venison and onions, green chilies, taco sauce, crushed red peppers and shredded cheese. Top with black olives and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be divided and frozen before baking.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake.
Bake according to cake box directions or until it tests done.
Cool.

title: banker boyd's bread
directions: Mix 1 package of Red Star yeast and 1 cup of warm water.
(Let stand 10 minutes.)
Then, mix in the following: self-rising flour, sugar, corn oil and buttermilk.
Mix all together.
Pinch out in biscuit size and place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: homemade oreo ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs with electric mixer until thick.
Add sugar and beat until creamy, about 15 minutes.
Add sweetened condensed milk, half and half and cream.
Fold in Oreos.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer and finish filling container with milk if needed.
Prepare according to ice cream freezer directions.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix well with mixer and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
You can use loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until sides pull away from sides of pan.

title: company squash casserole
directions: Place squash and onion in boiling salted water to cover. Cover and cook 5 minutes; drain well and set aside.

title: chicken coating mix(better than your favorite restaurant makes!)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl until evenly distributed.
Spoon mixture into a small airtight container. Label.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Use within 6 months.
Makes about 1/2 cup of Chicken Coating Mix.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice.
Add jello and let set until it starts to thicken.
Stir in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Mix dates, nuts and candied fruits with 1 cup flour; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add 3 cups flour which have been sifted with the baking powder and salt.
Beat until creamy and flour.
Stir in fruit and nut mixture.
(Dough will be very stiff.)
Add vanilla.
Cook in a tube pan that has been lined with brown paper.
(You may use 2 loaf pans lined with paper.) Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Let cool in pan.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift flour, then add dry ingredients and sift again.
Mix water and Miracle Whip.
Add to dry ingredients and add vanilla. Bake 1/2 hour at 350° or until done in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Mix milks and vanilla.
Gradually beat in snow until ice cream is of desired consistency.
Serves 5.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix condensed milk and Cool Whip. Add cherry pie filling, undrained pineapple and lemon juice. Freeze. Thaw 1 hour before serving.

title: steak kabobs
directions: Cut meat into strips about 3/4-inch wide and 2-inches long; place in shallow baking dish.

Mix remaining ingredients except pineapple and green pepper; cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Remove beef strips from marinade, reserving marinade; thread 9 to 10-inch bamboo skewers using 5 pieces of meat.
Grill 4-inches from medium hot coals until meat is browned, 4 to 5 minutes on each side, basting with marinade.
Garnish with pineapple chunks and green peppers.

title: mama carrol's fried rice(great with chicken adobo)
directions: Follow package directions on rice.
You will need 4 cups cooked.
Set this aside.
Melt margarine in a small skillet. Saute onion in margarine and remove from skillet.
Scramble egg in remaining margarine.
Add egg and onion to rice.
Mix and slowly stir in soy sauce until rice is a medium brown color.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add eggs and gradually add lemon juice and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets about 20 minutes or until almost tender.
Cool, peel and cut in thick slices.
Place in greased shallow baking dish.
Combine sugars, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add orange concentrate and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter when melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in 375° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and crumble. Drain off fat.
Return 1 tablespoon fat to skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not browned.
Place bacon, onion and cheese in pie shell.
Blend together eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in pie shell.
Bake in oven at 375° until mixture is firm and light brown, about 45 minutes.

title: portman pudding(3 to 4 persons)
directions: Cream fat and sugar; add carrot, potato, flour, spice and soda.
Mix well together.
Add fruit.
Add water if necessary to make a stiff dropping consistency.
Steam for 2 hours at least.
A sweet that needs little sugar!
(GR)

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and Cool Whip together.
Stir until pudding is completely dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and all other remaining ingredients.
Let set about 1 hour and serve.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook onions and celery, then brown hamburger with onions and celery; drain.
Add all other ingredients; heat over medium heat. Simmer over low heat for an hour or so.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Put in saucepan or microwave and bring to a boil the butter or margarine, water and cocoa. Mix together eggs, soda, buttermilk, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour cocoa mixture over flour mixture.
Add buttermilk mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: saint patrick's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over ice.
Garnish with sliced green apples or green cherries.

title: cajun salt
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
May be stored in any sealable container and used in a salt shaker for table use (carefully).

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: what ever
directions: Cook sugar, eggs, dates and butter 10 minutes or until dates are mushy.
Add vanilla, salt, nuts and Rice Krispies; mix.
Take a small amount of mixture and make into ball.
Roll in coconut.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Peel the green from rind. Cut into cubes. Soak rind in salted water with alum overnight.
Drain. Cover with fresh water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and drain.
Mix sugar into 8 cups water and add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture becomes syrupy.
Add rind and bring to a slow boil. Cook until rind is tender.
Pack in jars and seal.
Do water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 quarts.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine and drop by teaspoons into hot grease.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Mix together yeast, sugar and water.
Set aside.
Sift together flour and salt.
Blend into flour mixture the margarine (or shortening).
Make a well in flour mixture.
Add yeast mixture and 2 well beaten eggs.
Blend well.
Place dough in greased bowl; turn to grease all sides.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight or for several hours.
Roll out or shape rolls.
Place in a greased pan.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours before baking.
Bake 10 minutes in 450° oven.
Unused dough may be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: chicken breasts with mushrooms
directions: Brown chicken in oil; remove from skillet.
Brown mushrooms; stir in soup, garlic and seasonings.
Place chicken back in skillet.
Pour soup over chicken and mushrooms.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein 30 g, fat 27 g, calories 391.
One serving = 4 meat, low-fat exchange, 1/2 bread starch exchange, 3 fat exchange.

title: beet jelly
directions: Add Sure-Jell to juice to bring to rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add sugar and boil 4 minutes.
Add raspberry Kool-Aid.

title: carrot, raisin and pineapple salad
directions: *Add small amount of pineapple juice, if needed.

title: deer (or beef) chili
directions: Brown meat.
Dump in everything else; adjust with water. Simmer to desired thickness.
Top with cubed Monterey Jack cheese, olives (black) and a big blob of sour cream.
Take Rolaids.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Cook beef and add sauce. Butter a glass 9 x 13-inch dish. Layer spaghetti, cheese, pepperoni and meat sauce, ending with cheese on top. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: best bean casserole
directions: Drain butter and kidney beans.
Partially fry bacon; remove from pan.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Saute onions until tender and then add rest of ingredients except beans. Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir several times.
Combine sauce with beans and bacon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes, covered and 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Layer ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
For the bottom layer, combine pinto beans, chiles, onion, black olives and chili powder. For the next layer, combine avocado, lemon juice, garlic and taco sauce.
Next spread sour cream over.
Top with grated Monterey Jack/Colby cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cherry delight
directions: Make pudding as directed.
Place layer of graham crackers on bottom of cake pan.
Next layer vanilla pudding on top of crackers.
Put whipped cream on top of pudding and put cherries on top of whipped cream.

title: glazed chicken bits
directions: Using a wire whisk, in small mixing bowl, combine honey, ketchup, soy sauce, lemon juice, ginger root and garlic.
In 8-inch microwavable glass pie plate, arrange the chicken cubes. Pour honey mixture over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: frozen bread rolls
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put nuts on bottom.
Pull first loaf of bread apart and put on top of nuts.
Sprinkle cinnamon on bread.
Melt margarine; mix in pudding, sugar and milk.
Pour over first loaf of bread dough.
Pull second loaf of bread dough apart and place on top pudding mixture.
Let raise.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs and oil and stir with wooden spoon until mixed well. Do not beat with mixer.
Add vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas; mix well.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool in pans.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix in given order.
Roll by hand in small balls.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Roll in some confectioners sugar while hot. Repeat when cool or before serving.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add the cake mix and pudding mix.
Blend together in a large bowl until thoroughly mixed.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in the chocolate chips and cherries.
Pour into a buttered Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be served with powdered sugar sprinkled on top.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: pork chop supper
directions: In skillet, brown chops.
Pour off excess grease.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.

title: apple cobbler cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, flour and baking powder.
Pour half the batter into a large greased oblong pan; batter will be thick.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Pour remainder of batter over pie filling.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Dust with powdered sugar.
"You can use homemade applesauce."

title: amazing pie
directions: Put all ingredients except coconut in blender.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour in greased pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top of pie.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chess cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 300°.

title: gob cake
directions: You will need 2 cookie sheet pans, lightly greased.

title: mints
directions: Mash the cheese.
Add flavoring and coloring.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Knead with hands until mixed.
Roll into marble size balls and dip into granulated sugar.
Press into molds, sugar side up, and unmold onto wax paper.
Makes about 50 mints.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine ingredients for sauce and heat until smooth.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: berry banana smoothies
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine all ingredients; cover and process until smooth.
Pour into chilled glasses; serve immediately.
Serves 3.

title: broiled fish fillets
directions: Arrange fish fillets, skin side up, on broiler pan.
Brush both sides of fish with margarine.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Turn once and baste with margarine.
If desired, season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to boil.
Stir; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal; stir.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper immediately.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine pumpkin and buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Bake in well-greased, paper-lined 9-inch square pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream or frost as desired.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add
egg and flavoring.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Chill dough for
1 hour.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake
on	greased cookie sheets until lightly
browned,
approximately
to
minutes.
Can
be sprinkled with sugar or decorations before baking or iced after baking.
Makes a very light flaky sugar cookie.
Bake at 375°.

title: ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Leave rolls intact and slice through all of them horizontally. Leave bottom layer in pan.
Place a layer of ham and a layer of cheese on top. Replace top layer.
Mix other ingredients and pour over the top. Wrap and let stand 5 hours or overnight.
If you let stand overnight, please refrigerate.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° in a 9-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve top with sauce.

title: mother's quick coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and flour like pie crust.
Save 3/4 of mix and set aside.
To remaining mix, add baking powder and mix well. Beat eggs; add to milk and vanilla.
Add to mix.
Take and set aside mix and add cinnamon to make crumbs to top the cake.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic in oil. Add ginger, pepper strips, bouillon, soy sauce, sherry and brown sugar (if desired). Bring to a full boil. Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Stir before serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: whole-wheat pancakes
directions: In medium bowl, stir dry ingredients together with a fork. Beat egg slightly into buttermilk and add to flour mixture with 1 tablespoon oil, mixing until moistened.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix once each day until the fifth day.
On the fifth day, make it into rolls and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
This is delicious and tastes like the beef stick you buy in the store.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Stir ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cinnamon ornaments(non-food)
directions: If your brown sugar gets hard, put it in a plastic Ziploc bag.
Add one slice fresh bread, close tightly and leave a day or two.

title: coconut pudding pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Set aside.
In the bowl of mixer, cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and flour and blend well.
Add coconut and vanilla and mix.
Pour into prepared pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.
A delicate and thin crust is formed during baking.
A cross between a pie and a pudding.

title: tupperware bread rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in the sugar, flour and the salt; beat until smooth.
Add the soft shortening, egg and 1 1/4 cups more flour; beat until smooth.
Scrape down sides of bowl and seal.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.

title: strawberry chantilly torte cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 (8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch) layer pans as directed on package.
Cool; split to make 4 layers.
In small mixer bowl, beat frosting mix (dry), cream cheese, milk and almond extract until smooth.
Slice strawberries lengthwise, reserving 1/2 cup of the outer for top layer.
Stack layers, spreading each with about 1/2 cup frosting and about 1/2 cup strawberries.
Place reserved strawberry slices, cut side down, on top layer.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving because of the cream cheese (refrigerate leftover cake).

title: apple snickers salad
directions: Chop apples.
Stir pudding and pineapple into Cool Whip.
Chop Snickers into bite size pieces.
Add Snickers, apples and nuts to Cool Whip.
Serve cold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, water and rice in long casserole.
Salt chicken and place on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for
1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: First mix Lipton dried onion soup mix with other soups.
Butter casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice on bottom of pan.
Place chicken on rice then add chicken broth and mushroom soup over all.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours, covered. Uncover and bake 30 minutes or more until chicken is brown in 375° oven.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: ham loaf or ham rolls
directions: Place over heat until dissolved.
Pour over meat loaf or rolls. Start oven at low temperature, 325°, for 1/2 hour. Increase heat to 350°.
Keep basting every 45 minutes until well done (nice and brown).

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine milk and cream of chicken soup.
Heat and add chicken. Cook broccoli in boiling salted water 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain, arrange in bottom of shallow, greased casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Pour chicken over broccoli and cheese. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted and brown.

title: better than butter
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender.
Blend on low and increase speed until smooth.
Scrape mixture into a container and refrigerate.

title: sinfully delicious
directions: Crush Oreos cookies using a rolling pin or a food processor and add butter once crushed.
Put mixture in a 13 x 9-inch dish and press into a crust.
Set in freezer for 15 minutes.
Add vanilla ice cream by slicing it and pressing it flat (using spatula and wax paper) over crust.
Pour fudge sauce over ice cream, then add Cool Whip to top it off and sprinkle nuts on top. Cover and put in freezer for at least 15 minutes.
Serves 12.
All ingredients can be altered to fit one's taste (i.e., different ice cream, cookie or topping).

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, celery seed, salt and pepper. Toss lightly.
Separate whites of hard-cooked eggs from yolks. Chop whites and add to potato mixture; chill.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together after cooking macaroni first.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake in casserole at about 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butter balls(cookies)
directions: Mix and refrigerate all ingredients for 2 hours.
Roll in balls 1 inch in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: hamburger mexican dip
directions: *If Ro-Tel tomatoes are not available, use 1 large can of tomatoes, reserve juice and add as needed.
Use small can green chilies and flavor to taste.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake slowly for 2 hours in an uncovered casserole dish at 300°.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Crumble ground beef in medium glass bowl.
Stir in onion.
Cook at High 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until beef is brown.
Stir once; drain.
Stir in 1 can tomato sauce, water, 1 tablespoon cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, at High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes. Stir in rice, let stand, covered, 5 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter. Mix sugar and cornstarch (or flour). Add to creamed butter, continue creaming. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and turn into oiled loaf pans and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and slice.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute salt pork and onions in large pan.
Add potatoes and 1 cup water.
Simmer 5 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Place fish on top of potatoes and onions.
Add remaining cup of water. Simmer until fish flakes easily when touched with a fork.
Add half and half and milk.
Stir in butter, salt and pepper.
Heat through over low heat and serve.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Wash rice well under hot water.
Brown sausage and onion.
Add all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marble squares
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Combine oleo, water and chocolate in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, sour cream and soda.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter.
Cut through batter to marbleize.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and bake at 375° for 25 to 31 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, apricot nectar, oil, sugar and eggs on low speed until well blended, then on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan and bake in a 350° oven until done.
Remove from oven; let cool slightly, then remove from pan.

title: best ever baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon in large ovenproof container.
Lay bacon strips on top.
Place on smoker grid and smoke cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours or 4 hours in oven at 250°.

title: yummy chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
In a saucepan, melt butter and add water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Add this to mixture of flour and sugar; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oven dinners
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Put into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Drop frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with dry pudding and brown sugar.
Pour melted margarine over rolls. Top with nuts.
Let stand until rolls double.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: kris' beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add ham, ketchup, salt, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and the can of pork and beans.
Drain liquid from the lima, butter and kidney beans and add to mixture. Add molasses to taste and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form ball and roll in ground nuts or parsley.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: apple crisp delight
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in buttered Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over apples.
Add 5 to 6 tablespoons of water.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ham, pork, bread crumbs, eggs and milk.
Shape into meat balls.
Combine brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and water; bring to a boil.
Pour sauce over ham balls in pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well; form into ball and chill.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Bake white cake as
directed on box and cool.
Prong it and pour pineapple over
cake.
Mix
cream
cheese and vanilla pudding and spread over cake.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut over top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in butter for 3 - 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.
Place rice in a greased 8-in square baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over; do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 325 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
8 - 10 servings.

title: girl scout stew
directions: Use fat to brown ground beef and peeled, chopped onion.
Pour off fat.
Add soup and ketchup.
Cover pot and continue cooking until meat is completely cooked.
Serve over hamburger buns, split.
Serves 8.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain peas and put in a baking dish.
Drain the asparagus and save the juice and add asparagus to the peas.
Mix the flour with a small amount of milk to make a paste.
Melt the butter in a pan and add the flour paste.
Add remaining asparagus juice and cheese to the butter mixture and mix until melted.
Pour over casserole. Grate extra cheese on top along with cornflake crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Squeeze grated zucchini by handfuls to remove excess water. Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch bread pans. Spray with Pam and/or grease.

title: ham roll
directions: Spread ham, cheese and onion on thin layer of bread dough. Roll like cinnamon roll and connect end to make a circle.
Snip with scissors every 1 1/2-inches or so.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Take out; glaze with egg whites and sesame seed.
Put back in oven for an additional 15 minutes.

title: walnut grove toffee
directions: Butter a metal cookie sheet.
Combine butter, sugar, water and salt in a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches 236° (soft ball stage).
Stir in 2/3 cup walnuts.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 290°.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness with a greased spatula.
Sprinkle chips over top of toffee.
Let soften.
Spread evenly over surface of candy.
Quickly sprinkle with other 2/3 cup walnuts.
Cool several hours.
Break into pieces.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Add strawberries.
Add a few drops of food coloring for color.
Pour into baked crust.
Decorate with fresh strawberries.

title: mousse de chocolate
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
In a blender, mix gelatin, Alba '77 and water.
Add ice cubes and blend at high speed until smooth.
Pour into two dishes and chill.

title: cinnamon sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and lemon peel and beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: candied fruit slices
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugar and cream well. Blend in egg and vanilla. Add flour and blend well. Add pecans and fruit. Divide into 3 rolls. Chill. Slice and bake at 325° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: apple streusel mince pie
directions: Toss apples with 3 tablespoons flour and margarine.
Arrange in pastry shell.
Top with mincemeat.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in cold margarine until crumbly. Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle over mincemeat.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°; reduce oven temperature to 375° and continue baking 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: peach muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease or line 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups.
Reserve 2 tablespoons flour.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
In mixer bowl cream butter and sugar, adding eggs, one at a time, beating at low speed.

title: coconut cracker snacks
