directions: Line a jelly roll pan with foil; top with crackers side by side in a single layer.
In a small saucepan, melt oleo.
Stir in sugar; cook and stir for 1 minute.
Drizzle over entire surface of crackers.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until coconut is golden.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: mint brownies
directions: Mix sugar,
cup butter, flour, eggs, baking powder and chocolate syrup.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: nutritious cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Beat at medium speed until well blended, about 1 to 2 minutes.
By hand, stir rolled oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by well rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 28 cookies.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Sift flour twice.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add Crisco and cream.
Add eggs beating well.
Add milk, flavoring and baking powder mixing well.
Fold in flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until done.

title: spam buns
directions: Put all ingredients through grinder or food processor.
Spread buns; wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake for 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: caramel apple cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 3/4 cup apple filling.
Spoon remaining apple filling into crust.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs and beat well.
Pour over apple filling.
Bake 35 minutes or until center is set; cool.

title: brownies
directions: Melt cocoa and shortening together.
Gradually beat sugar into well-beaten eggs and add to cocoa mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; then sift again.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour and spread in greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. For a chewey brownie do not over-bake.
These are good frosted or without frosting.
Yield:
2-3 dozen.

title: creamy salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together (you may substitute light mayo or sour cream).
Chill 2 hours and stir.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine
flour,
salt
and
pepper.
Beat into sides of steak. Cut steak into equal parts. Brown on each side
in oil. Place onions on top of meat.
Mix remaining ingredients.	Pour over steak. Cover
and simmer slowly 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Mix ingredients. Add 2 tablespoons Hellmann's mayonnaise to make mixture spreadable.

title: ranch style lentil casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil.
(Note:
When using hamburger instead of ground beef, eliminate the oil.)
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour mixture into greased 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 475°.

title: fluffy cocoa frosting
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add cocoa.
Heat and boil 1 minute or until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Alternately add sugar and milk, beating to spreading consistency. Thicken with more powdered sugar or thin with more milk, if needed.
Blend in vanilla.
Fills and frosts two 8-inch round layers or one 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Dice bacon and fry until crisp.
Remove from pan and reserve 1/3 cup bacon fat.
Cook onions in fat until yellow.
Mix in flour, sugar, salt and celery seed, if used, and a dash of pepper. Stir in water and vinegar gradually.
Pour over sliced potatoes and add chopped celery, if used, and bacon.
Keep warm over hot water until ready to serve.

title: spicy collard greens
directions: In large stockpot, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until translucent.
Add salt, red pepper flakes, Tabasco sauce and sugar; mix well.
Add about 3 cups water.
Add collards.
Cover; cook for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add water if needed.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook hamburg, onion and green pepper.
Drain well.
Add catsup, mustard, brown sugar and hot sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve on rolls.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and jello real good with mixer.
Add the rest. Chill.

title: sausage brunch braid
directions: In a skillet over med. heat, cook sausage, onions, bell pepper and garlic until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender. Drain, add cream cheese and green onion. Cook and stir over low heat until cheese melt. Set aside.

Unroll crescent dough on a greased balking sheet. Press perforations together., Roll into a 12X10 in. rectangle. Spoon sausage mixture to within 3 in of long sides and 1 in of ends. On each long side cut 3/4 inch wide strips 3 in. into center starting at one end. fold alternating strips at an angle forming a braid.
Brush dough with beaten egg. Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until fluffy.
Stir together the dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to sugar mixture.
Add rhubarb last.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Bake at 350° for 38 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs, bananas and honey.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, beating just until blended. Stir in oats.
Fill 24 muffin pans lined with paper cups 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 24.

title: "wacky cake"
directions: Sift flour, salt, cocoa, soda and sugar into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in flour mixture.
In 1st hole, place vinegar. In 2nd hole, place vanilla and in 3rd hole, place oil.
Pour water over and stir.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: percolator wassail
directions: Put 1 gallon apple cider in the bottom of a 30 cup percolator. Into the basket put the cut up orange, cinnamon, whole allspice, cloves and brown sugar.
Percolate just as you would coffee. Great with doughnuts or Christmas cookies.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: To make meatballs, combine all ingredients (mixture will be soft) and shape into walnut size balls.
Place meatballs in a single layer on wax paper lined cookie sheets. Freeze until solid. Store frozen meatballs in freezer bags until ready to cook.
Makes 80 meatballs.
Use
Barbecued Meatball Sauce.

title: five-minute fudge
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
In
medium saucepan, combine evaporated milk with sugar and salt; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients, stirring until marshmallows melt. Pour into prepared pan; let cool.
To serve, cut into squares.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Chop candied cherries and pineapple and mix well.
Mash wafers and coat dry ingredients with the wafers.
Add milk; mix well.
It will be very stiff.
Press into 9 x 9-inch metal pan.
Set in refrigerator 12 hours.
Slice thin.

title: moist and creamy brownies
directions: Make pudding according to directions. Stir in powdered cake mix. Pour into a greased 9x13 pan. Sprinkle chips over the top. Bake 40 minutes at 425 degrees.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix dry jello and Cool Whip together.
Then add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Mix well and chill.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Brown meat slightly in oil.
Add celery, onions, pepper and broth.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Drain Chinese vegetables and mushrooms.
Add to mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce.
Add to hot mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Spoon into deep dish and garnish with green onions.
Serve over fried noodles.
Also can be served over cooked rice or Chinese noodles.

title: kansas city steak strips
directions: Cut steak into strips. Heat 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add mushrooms and onions, saute until tender, about 2 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon. Add remaining butter to skillet and add steak. Saute for 5 minutes or until browned. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until steak is tender. Blend flour with cold water, stir into skillet. Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat and return mushrooms and onion to skillet. Add green beans to skillet and mix well. Heat thoroughly, do not boil. Serve hot over buttered noodles. May also serve over cooked rice. Serves 6.

title: bean and cabbage salad
directions: In large bowl, mix well the red kidney and garbanzo beans, cabbage and green pepper.
Combine oil, vinegar, garlic, salt, dry mustard, sugar and pepper.
Pour dressing over bean mixture; toss lightly.
Cover and chill 4 to 6 hours.
(Stir occasionally.)

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Thoroughly combine the meat, bread crumbs, cheese, soup mix, salt, nutmeg and 1/2 cup of the milk.
Shape into small balls. Brown lightly in large skillet.
Cover and cook 20 to 25minutes or until done.
Remove meat; drain off excess fat, leaving 1/4 cup in skillet.
(For lower fat content, drain off all fat.)
Blend flour into fat; stir in remaining milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thick.
Return meatballs to skillet.

title: karen's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 1 stick butter to heavily coat bottom and lightly coat sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple rings in pan and place 1 cherry in the center of each ring.

title: persimmon fudge
directions: Combine persimmon pulp, margarine, evaporated milk and sugar and bring to boil (stirring constantly) until mixture gets to soft-ball stage (232° to 238°).
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Crme, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into greased 8 x 12 pan and let set until firm.

title: opera fudge
directions: Cook sugar,
syrup and milk
to
soft
ball stage.
Add condensed
milk,
stirring
slowly
all
the
time.
Continue cooking until mixture forms a soft ball.
Add salt and butter; let cool 5 minutes.
Stir and beat until thick.
Add nutmeats. Spread in buttered pan and cut in one-inch squares.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix in bowl the tomatoes, chili peppers, both soups and taco season powder; set aside. Put chips in bottom of dish; put chicken on top of chips. Spread mixture on top of chicken. Sprinkle onion and green pepper on top of that. Put cheese on top of onions and peppers. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Combine ground chuck, onions, green peppers, rice, salt and pepper in large
skillet
and
brown.
Pour off any excess fat after it has cooked.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce and 1 cup of the cheese.
Cook
on
low heat about 15 minutes.
Pour contents into casserole
dish
and
top with remaining cheese. Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: toasted cheese sandwiches
directions: Toast your bread in toaster.
Butter afterwards, if desired. Put a couple of slices of cheese between 2 slices of bread.
Put on plate.
Microwave about 12 seconds.
Presto, a fast toasted cheese sandwich.

title: texas chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Bring to boil oleo, Crisco oil, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix together and pour into a greased and floured jelly-roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fried turnips
directions: Peel and cut up as many turnips as you would potatoes.
Put in skillet with hot bacon drippings.
Sprinkle sugar over turnips. Cover until sugar melts.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Finish frying the same as you would potatoes.

title: heavenly potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes for 20 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Peel and grate potatoes into 3-quart casserole.
Mix in onion.
Pour butter and cream over all.
Season to taste and stir gently. Cover and chill overnight.
Remove casserole from refrigerator 2 hours before baking.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with this mixture, pressing firmly into pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and softened margarine.
Beat 15 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Spread on top of crumb pastry.
Slice bananas over top.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Top with whipped topping, pecans and cherries.
Chill several hours before cutting into squares.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Serves 20.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper the steak to taste.
Flour lightly.
Brown steak on both sides.
Put green peppers and onions over steak and add tomatoes.
Cook in a moderate oven for 2 hours, using a covered pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together; drain.
Add mushrooms, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Let simmer on low for 5 minutes. Add flour, stirring constantly.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Add sour cream immediately before serving.
Serve over previously boiled egg noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot chicken sandwich
directions: Place 4 slices bread on a single layer in a shallow 9 x 9-inch greased dish.
Combine all ingredients except eggs, soup, and milk.
Spread over bread and top with remaining bread.
Combine eggs and 1 1/2 cups milk and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, combine soup and 1/2 cup milk and pour over bread.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook
water,
syrup,
sugar
and
butter together until syrup threads.
Add
nuts and cook at a high temperature until peanuts pop
and syrup turns golden brown.
Take off stove and add baking soda,
stirring
well.
Pour
on
a greased cookie sheet.
Cool and press on bottom of the sheet to loosen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with fresh sliced fruit.

title: fish ring
directions: Boil fish; let cool.
Separate in small pieces; add bread crumbs and well-beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Place in well-buttered ring mold.
Steam 1 1/2 hours, or until firm.
Serve with cream sauce; cover with hard-boiled eggs put through a ricer.
Use green peas in center of ring.
To prevent odor of fish while cooking, squeeze lemon juice on both sides of fish.
Wrap in wax paper; let stand in refrigerator 1 hour before cooking.

title: strawberry and peach trifle
directions: Drain strawberries and peaches.
Tear angel food cake in small pieces.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Put a layer of cake in bottom of pan.
Layer pudding, peaches, strawberries and Cool Whip.
Continue layering until all is used up.
Save a few strawberries to put on top.
I finish up with Cool Whip and a layer of strawberries on top.

title: cincinnati chili(served over thin spaghetti.)
directions: In large pan, bring beef broth to boil.
Gradually add ground beef to broth, separating meat into small pieces.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Mix in rest of ingredients; bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, 1 hour stirring occassionaly.
Refrigerate overnight and skim off fat.
Reheat slowly and serve over spaghetti.

title: maple pecan pound cake
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each one. Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Add flavoring and nuts. Fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Pour filling into shell.
Combine caramels, butter, lemon juice and milk over low heat. Stir constantly until caramels melt. Pour over pie filling.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Cream together light brown sugar, shortening and egg. Thoroughly stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with 1 cup sour milk.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups diced rhubarb and spread into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle on topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Blend eggs, water, oil and pumpkin and gradually add dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 48 muffins.

title: chocolate cherry cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine softened cream cheese, oleo and sugar, mixing well.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until set.

title: phil's poppy seed triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter and sugar in a mixer or a food processor.
Add the beaten egg and mix.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla and orange extract.
Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: collard greens
directions: Wash collards thoroughly. Remove stems and tear leaves into small pieces.
Place collards, meat, onion, garlic and seasonings in large pot.
Add about 4 cups water, more if necessary.
Cook slowly about 2 hours or until greens and meat are tender.

title: apple cranberry shortcake
directions: Put apples, cranberries, water, sugar, cinnamon and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until apples are tender.
Bake shortcake in two 8-inch layers.
Put hot apple mix between layers and on top of hot shortcake.
Cut into wedges and serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients with wire whisk.
Scramble eggs with oil and add wet to dry.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Makes 2 to 3 loaves.

title: herb's apple butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Combine the flour, baking soda and baking powder and add alternately with the apple butter to the first mixture.
If needed, add up to 1 additional cup flour to make a stiff batter.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Place potatoes in a large pot with enough water to barely cover.
Add onions.
Cook over medium-high heat for 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium-low for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: In buttered
pan, place chicken, cover with sauerkraut. Top with Swiss	cheese.
Pour
dressing
evenly
over
cheese, cover with foil.	Bake
at
325°	for about 1 1/2 hours, serve sprinkled with chopped parsley.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Pour chicken broth into 1 1/2-quart microwaveproof bowl. Cover, microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with cold water.
Stir some of the hot broth into the cornstarch mixture.
Mix well.
Add rest of broth, stir well.
Add green onions and water chestnuts.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes or until it boils and is clear.
Remove from oven.
Pour beaten eggs through tines of a fork to make threads of eggs.
Stir well.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix the applesauce and cinnamon.
Mix to form dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Make hole for ribbon. Carefully put on rack to dry.
Let air dry for several days, turning occasionally.

title: pineapple baked meat balls
directions: Save pineapple juice.
Soak bread in water; combine beef, salt, onion, black pepper and bread.
Shape into balls.
Cook in shallow pan at 375° for 25 minutes; drain meat balls.
Spread drained pineapple chunks and thinly sliced bell pepper over meat balls. Combine brown sugar, ketchup, vinegar and syrup from pineapple and pour over meat balls.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef; drain grease.
Add taco seasoning mix, following directions on package.
Tear lettuce and add tomatoes, cheese, beef and crumbled tortilla chips.
Pour on desired amount of dressing and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: custard sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and blend.
Cool before serving.

title: chicken taco rice
directions: Cook rice; drain.
Set aside.
Add broth, tomato sauce and taco seasoning to chicken pieces.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Add corn; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with chips, cheese and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: madeleines(french tea cakes)
directions: Sift together the cake flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside.

title: vegetable ball
directions: It is most important to make sure all ingredients are well drained of excess liquid.
Use cheesecloth to strain pineapple and all vegetables.
After pineapple and vegetables are well drained, pour them into a large bowl.
Add cream cheese and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover bowl and place in refrigerator and chill until firm enough for you to shape into a ball.
Roll ball in 1/2 cup pecans.
Serve with Sociables crackers.

title: chicken with mushroom sauce
directions: In a skillet, saute mushrooms in butter until tender.
With a slotted spoon, remove mushrooms and set aside.
Reserve butter in the skillet.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in large pan.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk and water.
Add chocolate.
Cook and stir over medium heat until chocolate is completely melted and mixture boils. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into baked crust.
Chill pie at least 2 hours before serving.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix together egg, vanilla, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Set aside.
Combine milk and evaporated milk; stir in rice and egg mixture.
Heat all ingredients to a boil or until thickens, stirring constantly.
Pour in bowl, sprinkle with cinnamon and refrigerate.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add potatoes and grated chocolate.
Sift flour, baking powder and spices together and add alternately with milk.
Add nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or 2 (10-inch) round pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Test with a broom straw.
This recipe is over 100 years old.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add sugar slowly.
Mix in pumpkin plus lemon juice.
Fold in flour plus cinnamon.
Pour into greased and floured flat pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up and cool in refrigerator.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix ingredients in order given; marinate for at least 12 hours before serving.
Drain off excess liquid and serve on bed of cold lettuce.
Garnish with lemon wedges and parsley.

title: berry-cream tart
directions: Mix flour with sugar in a large bowl.
Cut in margarine until size of peas.
Form with hands into a ball of dough.
Press dough firmly in bottom and up sides of ungreased 10-inch tart pan with removable bottom.
Brush bottom of pastry with lightly beaten egg white.
Bake on center rack in preheated 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely, then remove rim.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. After cake is done and still hot, mix 1 cup orange juice and 1 cup sugar together.
Pour over top of cake.

title: batter for fried cauliflower
directions: Cut cauliflower into florets. Mix together the eggs and milk; dip cauliflower in egg mixture.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Roll cauliflower in crumb mixture.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: crepe suzettes
directions: Combine
eggs, milk, flour, sugar and salt.
Beat until very smooth.
Drop just enough batter on well-greased griddle to make thin consistency.
Brown slowly on both sides.
Spread lightly with desired filling.

title: cinnamon pinwheel cookies
directions: In a bowl, make a well with flour.
Then place yeast and cream.
Beat in eggs and pinch of salt.
Mix all together by hand. Cover dough and refrigerate 1 hour.
Take out 1/4 of batter; leave rest in refrigerator.
Roll dough into circle.
Pat with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up into a tight jelly roll.
Continue until dough is used up.
Keep rolls in refrigerator until done.
Sprinkle sugar on cutting board.
Place rolls on board and slice them around 1/4-inch thick and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: pear jello mold
directions: Beat jello while adding hot water.
Add to cream cheese.
Add cold water and beat.
Add pear syrup.
Arrange pears in jello mold and add jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: hearty beef and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef.
Drain. Combine soup, milk, half the cheese and seasonings.
Add the ground beef, broccoli, 1/2 can of Durkee onions and tomato.
Pour onto potatoes.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Preparation time: 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: walnut powder puffs
directions: Cream butter with 1/3 c. 10x sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour, then nuts.
Shape into tiny balls, about 1 inch in diameter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheets in 350° oven for about 12-15 minutes, until firm but not brown.
Roll in 10x sugar after removing from sheets.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Crumble 1/2 of cake.
Top with 1/2 can pineapple, 1/2 can cherry pie filling and 1/2 of pudding. Repeat this procedure.
Top with Cool Whip.
This fills a large bowl and looks pretty in a glass bowl.

title: chocolate filled oatmeal bars
directions: Mix together and save half of this for the top, then put 1/2 in bottom of a pan.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peggy's brunswick stew
directions: Start with pot 3/4 full of water.
When boiling, add beans and water they were soaked in
(precooked or preheated, if desired). After cooking awhile, add potatoes.
Next, add all peppers and onions, blended.
When potatoes are done, add tomatoes.
Add meat and corn last.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and chill before serving several hours.

title: cheese and lunch meat stacks
directions: Stack cheese and lunch meat, alternating each layer.
Trim around edges to make square.
Place toothpicks through all slices, about 3/4-inch apart.
Slice between toothpicks.

title: wilma's oriental chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients thoroughly.
Place lettuce leaf on plate. Top with salad, avocado slices and cherry tomatoes.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Beat eggs, yogurt, milk and cornstarch. Stir in remaining ingredients except broccoli.
Spray a 9-inch baking pan with Pam.
Put broccoli in pan and pour mixture over it. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: georgia squash casserole(a family favorite)
directions: Blend onion and milk.
Add 1/3 stick oleo.
Beat until oleo melts.
Pour over bread and mash with potato masher.
Add squash. Mix well.
Add eggs and pimiento and seasonings.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers and other 1/3 stick oleo.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds, if desired.
Bake at 425° until set and lightly browned.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco well.
Add sugar in 3 parts and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Fold in 1/2 of milk and 1/2 flour and mix, then add other half.
Add vanilla and mix. Pour in greased tube pan.
Sprinkle pan with flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together; add beaten egg.
Add soda to buttermilk and stir.
Add to first mixture.
Work in gradually enough flour to make stiff dough.
Knead until smooth (6 or 7 times).
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick and cut with 3-inch biscuit cutter.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top if desired.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes or until very lightly brown.
Remove from pan immediately and cool on linen towel.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients and form into small bite size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Place in casserole dish and pour your favorite spaghetti sauce over them.
Heat before serving.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in oil.
Add enough milk to make stiff dough.
Thinly roll out dough on lightly floured board into 2 (10 x 18-inch) rectangles.
Spread on sausage and roll up lengthwise.
Chill well and slice.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: diet fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, but do not drain off juice.
Cut up apple and orange and mix pudding and jello dry into mixture.
Place in refrigerate for about 1 hour.

title: mocha frosting
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt margarine.
Stir in cocoa and instant coffee, dissolved in 1 tablespoon warm water.
Remove from heat.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar.
Add additional warm water if needed.

title: horseshoes
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add 1 cup flour and mix well; let stand 1/2 hour.
Mix butter and 3 cups flour; add to yeast mixture.
Then add another 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on granulated sugar, about 1/4-inch thick. Cut in strips 1/4 x 3-inches, shaped like horseshoes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate angel food dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler over simmering water. Slowly add beaten egg yolks and stir well.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat egg whites stiff; add sugar and fold into cooled chocolate mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and pecans. Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with angel food slices.
Top with chocolate mixture.
Continue layering cake slices and chocolate mixture.
Chill 6 hours or longer.
May garnish with whipped cream.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Combine cake mix and butter; mix until crumbly.
Take out 2/3 cup of mixture and set aside.
Press remaining mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange apple slices over mixture in pan. Blend sour cream and egg; spread over apples.
Combine the 2/3 cup of dry reserved mix with the 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Stir to mix.
Sprinkle over all, distributing the topping evenly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm. This is a delicious coffee or brunch cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, butter and vanilla flavoring.
Add white sugar and white syrup.
Bake at 325° until firm in middle.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place the garlic and hot peppers in the bottom of clean hot jars.
Pack firmly with clean young okra pods from which only part of the stem has been removed.
Stem end must be open.
Add dill seed after packing jars.

title: blond brownies
directions: To flour, add baking powder, soda, salt and sift again.
Add nuts.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl, stir well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 8 inch square baking dish.
Separate biscuits and arrange over chicken mixture.
Bake at 450 degrees for 20 minutes or until golden and bubbly, covering loosely with aluminum foil after 12 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Roll crackers and spread in bottom of glass dish.
Cut up marshmallows and stir into hot milk until marshmallows melt.
Whip the cream and add drained pineapple, then add marshmallow mixture. Pour over cracker crumbs and refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion.
Mix broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz and soup.
Mix in margarine and onion.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot coco mocha
directions: Mix ingredients together.
To serve:
Pour 3 tablespoons into coffee mug.
Add coffee to within 1-inch of top of mug.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with orange twist.

title: creamy corn
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, butter and onion salt in a saucepan; warm over low heat until cheese melts.
Add drained corn and heat through.
Pour into serving dish; sprinkle with parsley and paprika.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 Pam-sprayed loaf pans.

title: pecan caramel rolls
directions: Let dough rise until doubled.
Combine 3 tablespoons butter, 1/4 cup brown sugar, water and syrup.
Spread in a 10 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients until creamed, then stir in dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: garden chicken salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together until well blended.
Toss vegetables in large bowl with dressing mixture.
Arrange lettuce leaves on platter.
Place vegetable mixture on top of lettuce leaves.
Arrange chicken on top of salad ingredients.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, except potato chips.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbled up potato chips.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; then add cream style corn.
Top with Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan bars
directions: Melt butter. Add brown sugar and mix.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix.
Mix dry ingredients and add to butter mix.
Mix entire ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: kentucky relish
directions: (*Or you may use pickling spices instead.)
Pour over pickles while hot.

title: tex-mex chili
directions: Saute onions in large frying pan.
Add sliced steak and sear meat; drain.
Put in large pot.
Add the rest of the ingredients; bring to a boil, mixing constantly.
Lower flame to low; simmer all day long, stirring often.

title: wonderful hearty cheddar chowder
directions: Combine water and bouillon cubes in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour and cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir cheese sauce, pimento and hot sauce into vegetable mixture.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated. Do not boil.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.
One (8 ounce) serving equals 400 calories.

title: coffee cake squares
directions: Cream margarine in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well.
Add eggs.
Combine sour cream and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and stir well.
Add flour mixture and vanilla to creamed mixture, beating well.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar, pecans and cinnamon.

title: chicken st. john
directions: Cook chicken; boil for 30 minutes or so.
Drain and lay breast side by side in a casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Add sherry.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil in saucepan.
Add peanuts. Cook until water has evaporated and peanuts are evenly coated, stirring frequently.
Spread on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Yields 10 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients and put into crust.
Chill at least three hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together soup mix, rice, cream of chicken soup and water; place in a baking dish.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, bananas and eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients and mix with banana mixture.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: larry's muffin pan oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Dry by rounded tablespoonfuls into greased muffin pans.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes for delicious, chewy cookies.

title: freezer berry jam
directions: Let combined mixture stand for 1 hour.
Put in sterilized jars.
Seal and freeze.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with milk.
Roll 1/8 inch thick, cut with large cutter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in hot oven for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in eggs one at a time. Add vanilla, flour and baking powder to chocolate mixture.
Chill well, 3 to 4 hours.
Roll into teaspoon size balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet 2 inches apart. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: ugly dip
directions: Chop everything up and dump into a bowl.
Serve with scoops (corn chips).

title: honey dijon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in dressing, making sure well coated.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese and coat chicken.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Serves 8.

title: low-fat ice cream
directions: Mix milks together with slow mixer or whisk.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add fruit and juice, then add pudding mix.
Mix well. Freeze according to directions with the ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: rice cheddar
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add rice and pimentos. Cook over low heat until rice is thoroughly heated.
Stir in cheese. Add salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, lightly beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients and stir until well combined.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish or 3 quart shallow oval casserole.

title: grandpa's deep fried crappie fillets
directions: Mix all but flour and corn meal.
Soak fillets in mix 30 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients.
Coat fillets.
Dip in marinade and re-coat if desired.
Let stand 30 minutes, re-coat in corn meal mixture.
Lower into preheated deep fryer at 360° and cook until fish floats.
Serve with onion slices, lemon pepper or tartar sauce.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Cut shortening into flour.
Blend together vinegar, water and egg and add to dry ingredients.
Toss until moistened and forms a ball.
Divide into 4 portions.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in a Ziploc bag. Freeze until ready to use.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: sweet chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan and heat.
Arrange chicken parts in baking dish.
Pour heated sauce over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
When chicken is tender, poke holes in meat with fork.
Baste frequently.
Five minutes before chicken is done, pour orange and pineapple over meat; do not use juice, just fruit.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put butter, chocolate chips and marshmallow cream (don't cook).
Combine sugar and milk; slowly heat, stirring constantly.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Add vanilla and pour over uncooked ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Add walnuts.
Pour into buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in jar.
To serve, add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup of hot water.

title: white cake supreme
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat shortening until soft.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gently fold into mixture.
Add mayonnaise.
Pour into lightly greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Frost with Creamy White Frosting.

title: wheat-nut rolls
directions: Soak the cracked
wheat in the 1 cup cold water and 1/2 teaspoon salt for
several	hours
or
overnight.
In
a large bowl, dissolve the	yeast
in
the	warm
water;
stir
in the scalded and cooled	milk,
sugar,
oil,
2	teaspoons salt and beaten egg.
Add
the
soaked
wheat mixture.
Mix in flour to make a stiff
dough.
Turn	out
on
a floured board and knead until the dough
is
smooth
and
elastic.	Place in a greased bowl and let rise in a warm place until almost doubled.
Punch down, roll out
on	a
lightly floured board, and cut into any desired roll shapes.
Arrange
on
a greased baking sheet; let rise until almost
doubled.
Brush	tops with melted butter or salad oil.	Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 30.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: In large bowl, whisk together first 4 ingredients.
Stir in green onion and sesame seed.
Add vegetables; toss.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: canned squash
directions: In a pan, put squash, onions and salt.
Cover with ice; let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Cook vinegar, sugar, seed and turmeric; bring to boil.
Add squash; cook for 3 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: baked chicken breast or turkey breast
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat butter and oil in baking dish until melted.
Place chicken in dish, turning to coat with butter. Arrange skin side up.
Bake 1 hour.
Heat soup, cream and wine, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tarragon leaves, Worcestershire sauce, chervil leaves, garlic powder and mushrooms.
Remove chicken from oven; drain fat from dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly and cook 15 to 20 minutes longer or until tender.

title: caroline chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, 1 egg and pecans together; press in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Heat pineapple, water, sugar and salt to a boiling point.
Add gelatin and cream cheese. Stir until dissolved.
Set until firm. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed graham crackers.

title: tuna potato chip casserole
directions: Put a layer of potato chips on bottom of a 9 x 13 inch dish. Mix mushroom soup and milk together in a bowl, pour over chips and tuna.
Add another layer of potato chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
The last five minutes of baking, garnish with cheese and let melt.

title: coffee cake
directions: Put cake mix, oil, water, pudding and eggs into a bowl and beat for 10 minutes.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Mix sugar, cocoa and ground cinnamon together and sprinkle over batter and swirl in, using a knife.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Turn upside-down on plate to cool.
Needs no frosting.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add flour, stir and cook until smooth.
Add cream cheese, stir until smooth.
Beat eggs; add milk, cheese, baking powder, salt and sugar, stir until well blended. Add flour/cream cheese mixture, blend well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: poached salmon steaks
directions: In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch flameproof casserole, bring all ingredients except the salmon steaks slowly to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove veggies with a slotted spoon.
Add salmon steaks to casserole; simmer gently for 5 to 6 minutes until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Remove salmon with a slotted spatula.
Serve immediately or cool to room temperature and refrigerate, covered.
Strain and reserve cooking liquid for recipes that call for fish stock or court bouillon.
May be frozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions and chilies in margarine.
Add chicken until heated through.
Take off fire and stir in cream cheese.
Put mixture into tortillas and roll.
Place rolls in baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Cover with whipping cream and bake at 350° until thick and bubbly.
Cover with cheese and place in oven until melted. Serve with picante sauce.

title: banana coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Check with toothpick to see if done.

title: easy beef enchilada
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Brown beef. Stir in 3/4 cup enchilada sauce and 1 cup cheese.
Spoon filling into tortilla. Roll and place seam side down in 13 x 9 pan. Place remaining sauce over top and 1/2 cup cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jade molded salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water and cool until it begins to set.
Fold remaining ingredients into gelatin and pour into ring mold or individual molds.
Serves 12.

title: coconut cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the butter; blend in the cream cheese. Add confectioners sugar alternately with milk, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla. Spread frosting over top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle coconut over frosting.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6-inch), melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle in crumbs; stir well.
Press on bottom of dish.
In medium bowl, mix together the sweetened condensed milk, sour cream and lemon juice; spread evenly over crumbs.
Spoon pie filling evenly over creamy layer. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until set.
Cool slightly.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Stir in orange juice, pineapple juice and bananas.
Freeze in milk cartons until ready to serve.
Tear open cartons.
Pour frozen mixture in punch bowl.
Add 2 liters (or more) 7-Up.

title: alabama cornish hens
directions: Drain oranges and reserve juice.
Cook rice according to directions, using juice as part of the water.
Stir in curry powder, parsley, 1/2 cup butter and the oranges.
Stuff hens lightly, then secure opening with skewer.
Place on broiler pan. Combine with the rest of the butter and the wine, then brush with butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting frequently.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Dissolve sugar in liquid before adding dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple delight pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and pour into 2 pie shells.
Chill approximately 45 minutes before serving.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Add fish (more or less to your appetite).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs to cover.
Dot with butter. Cook in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper, garlic and celery in oil in skillet. When tender, add rice.
Stir until well mixed and grains are semi-fried.
Add tomatoes, seasonings and hot water.
Stir until well mixed.
Do not cover.
Cook over very low heat until rice is dry, light and fluffy, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Add 2 cups crushed potato chips on top of casserole and bake another 10 minutes.

title: triple-chocolate dessert
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Mix pudding using 4 cups of milk instead of 3.
Crush Skor bars.
Divide cake into thirds.
Crumble 1/3 of cake into large bowl.
Layer 1/3 pudding on top.
Top with 1/3 (8 ounces) Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 1/3 crushed Skor bars on top.
Repeat 2 more times.

title: chili frito pie
directions: Crush Fritos and put in bottom of baking dish.
Then put in onion and half of cheese.
Spread chili on next.
Top with rest of cheese and Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: garden harvest squares
directions: Spread crescent roll dough flat on ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake as directed on package (about 11 minutes at 375°).
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing until smooth.
Spread onto cooled rolls.
Cut into squares before adding chopped vegetables to prevent knocking vegetables off while cutting.
Add any chopped raw vegetables such as broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, green peppers, radishes, etc. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend in oil, add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Thinly roll out dough on lightly floured surface. Cut into two (10 x 18-inch) rectangles.
Spread on sausage and roll up lengthwise.
Chill well and slice.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: jim's applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together (about 2 minutes).
Put into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook 60 minutes in 350° oven. Frost with vanilla cream frosting or cream cheese frosting. (Freezes well, too.)

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together to make crumbs the flour, brown sugar, shortening and salt.
Make liquid part with molasses, egg yolk, soda and boiling water.
Put the liquid into a 10-inch unbaked pie crust. Top with the crumbs.
Bake in 300° oven until crumbs fill the pie pan, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Add butter, cheese and seasoning.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add warm milk to eggs. Mix well.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix like bread dough, kneading thoroughly.
Repeat after refrigerating 24 hours.
Shape into 4 loaves and bake 7 to 9 hours at 150°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cocoa.
In microwavable deep dish, microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave for 5 minutes more.
Add butter and vanilla.
Whip until creamy.
Serve over ice cream hot or let cool.
Use Spanish peanuts on top for extra special good eating!
Makes 5 servings.

title: cereal peanut bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan, combine corn syrup, brown sugar and dash of salt.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Stir in Rice Krispies, corn flakes and chocolate chips.
Press into prepared pan.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch casserole or cake pan and line with sauerkraut, then cooked noodles.
Mix soup, mustard and mayonnaise and spread over casserole.
Spread onion, corned beef and Swiss cheese on top. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: low-fat broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Microwave onion until slightly tender.
In large bowl, mix cooked rice, cubed cheese, onion, cream of mushroom soup and water chestnuts.
Slightly steam broccoli; add to mixture.
Pour mixture into casserole dish sprayed with nonstick type spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: calzone
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients except dough and oil.
Roll dough into 14-inch circle.
Add filling to 1/2 of the dough, leaving about 1 1/2-inches around outer edge.
Moisten edge with water and fold dough over to make edges meet.
Roll edge slightly to seal.
Brush entire surface with oil lightly.
Reduce oven to 375° and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Pour warmed pizza sauce before serving.

title: broccoli noodle salad
directions: *Use saltless seeds if you are watching your salt.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Set in refrigerator until chilled.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and cracker crumbs.
Add corn, all seasonings and melted butter.
Mix together and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: reese's peanut butter brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

Melt butter. Add peanut butter; stir until peanut butter is melted. Stir in sugar and vanilla. Add eggs; beat well with spoon. Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well. Remove 1 3/4 cups batter; stir cocoa into this part. Spread chocolate batter into prepared pan. Spread remaining batter over top.

title: ruby's what we gonna have for supper
directions: Brown meat over high heat in a 10-inch skillet; drain.
Add ingredients (except noodles).
Stir to combine and simmer over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Stir as needed and lower heat if necessary.
Mix 2 tablespoons of cornstarch and water as thickening agent.
Add to mixture to thicken sauce.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chop-vegetable casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil 3 to 5 minutes on each side; arrange chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine soup and remaining ingredients; spoon over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dana's easy french toast
directions: Mix eggs and low-fat milk into a square dish.
Stir until blended.
Dip slices of dry bread into batter.
Fry toast in a lightly buttered nonstick skillet until golden brown.
Sprinkle toast with cinnamon and top with syrup.
Serve with a cold glass of milk.

title: crepes(french pancakes)
directions: In small bowl combine milk, flour, eggs, a sprinkle of salt and oil.
Beat until smooth and lumps are gone.
Brush small skillet lightly with salad oil.
Heat skillet over medium heat.
You can tell when skillet is hot enough by sprinkling a little cold water on it.
If water sizzles and rolls off pan it's ready.
Remove skillet from heat.
Pour in a little batter (about 2 tablespoons); tilt pan so batter covers the bottom evenly.
Cook over medium heat for 3 or 4 minutes, or until richly browned on underside.
Check the color by lifting with spatula.
Turn over crepe with spatula. Cook another minute or two, to brown on the other side lightly. Turn out onto serving platter.
Spread with raspberry preserves. Fold in half, then in half again, like a handkerchief.
Sprinkle with some confectioners sugar.
Serve at once, or keep warm in a low oven (set at 300°) while you're making the others.
You can make 7 more crepes with the remaining batter.
Brush the pan with oil and heat it again before making each one.
Before serving, sprinkle each pancake with sugar again.

title: drunk franks
directions: Cut franks into bite size pieces and combine all ingredients together and heat.
Let cool.
Heat to serve.
Best made 24 hours in advance.

title: egg salad
directions: Mash or grind eggs.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix and make sandwiches.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat ingredients together with spoon. If soft, add more biscuit mix. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: stuffed baker
directions: Scrub the potatoes.
Pat them dry.
Prick the surface with a fork.
Using 2 tablespoons of the butter, grease the potatoes. Bake at 425° for 1 hour. Grease a casserole with 1 tablespoon butter to hold the potatoes in one layer.
Cut 1/4-inch off the top of potato. Scoop out the pulp of the potato leaving some in the skin (small spoon works).
Mash the pulp with the remaining ingredients (reserve 1 teaspoon butter) and mound it back into the potato.
Place them in casserole dish.
Divide the butter on top and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Place flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix. Add 1 c. of milk and blend.
Melt the margarine and pour over the top of the mixture.
Pour peaches (juice and peaches) on top.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Pour sherry over chicken and marinate at room temperature 1/2 hour, turning once or twice.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Pat dry and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook in margarine about 4 minutes on each side or until tender.

title: chocolate chip cookie pie desserts
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cumin rice
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, saute onion, green pepper and rice in bacon grease.
When onion is transparent and golden brown, stir in everything else.
Cover with a tight fitting lid.
Turn heat to simmer and cook 20 minutes.

title: frozen pumpkin dessert
directions: Line a pan with cookie crumbs.
Add ice cream to pumpkin mixture.
Add spices.
Spread filling on cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Freeze.

title: shrimp, broccoli and carrots (sometimes onions) over pasta
directions: Cover the bottom of a heavy skillet with olive oil (about 1/4 cup).
Using medium heat, add fresh minced garlic (according to your taste); add broccoli, carrots and onion.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all but
soup.
Make balls and brown; put in baking dish. Pour soup over
top
and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown meat in butter in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Add next 7 ingredients. Mix well and cook, covered, 20 minutes until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in cheese.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Chill for an 1 hour and serve with crackers or chips.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough and place on pizza pan. Bake for 12 minutes at 350°. Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup of sugar and vanilla and spread on cooled cookie. Wash and slice fruit. Arrange in a circular pattern. Combine orange juice, 2/3 cup of sugar and cornstarch. Cook on low-medium heat until thick. Spoon over fruit. Chill for 30 minutes. Slice and serve.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in bowl. Add onion, lemon juice, garlic powder, and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Put in lasagne dish. Layer crab on top of cream cheese mixture.
Pour cocktail sauce over top.
Serve with bland crackers.

title: dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix vanilla pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour over the graham crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Melt chocolate chips with 1/4 cup of milk in microwave or double boiler. Pour over top of graham crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: deviled crab
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in crab shells; sprinkle with additional cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: tagliatelle(for an army)
directions: This recipe feeds an army.
I like to use a large turkey pan that has been greased.

title: skillet chicken supreme
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken.
Remove from pan.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add soup, milk and tarragon.
Return chicken to pan.
Cover and boil until chicken is done.
Add beans.
Cook until done. Serve over noodles, mashed potatoes or rice.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwiches
directions: Divide bread.
Spread peanut butter on one slice and jelly on the other.
Place the prepared slices together with the peanut butter and jelly on the inside.
Cut finished sandwiches into 2 parts.
Serve with cold milk.
Also very good with macaroni and cheese.
(If served with macaroni and cheese, it is suggested to have husband prepare the sandwiches as well.)

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with wire whip.
Add condensed milk and continue beating.
Add sugar and blend again.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour half and half, milk and continue to blend.
Pour into ice cream bucket.
Finish filling with milk until you reach the full line. Pour ice and salt around ice cream and freeze until firm.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours, better if overnight.
Serve with croutons on top or crusty French bread on the side.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add a little sugar and lemon; brown in the oven.
Cook all ingredients until thick.
Pour into baked crust. Add egg whites and brown.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Press into pan. Chill.

title: beef
directions: Trim fat off meat.
In a skillet, heat butter until lightly brown.
Add meat.
Brown well on all sides.
Sprinkle with half salt and pepper (salt can be reduced).
Reduce heat.
Cover and let meat cook for about 10 minutes, turning over during cooking time.
Remove meat and cover with foil.
Set aside.
Add water to pan and heat.
Scrape browning and strain juices.
Peel potatoes and slice thinly.
Layer potatoes on a slightly greased ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle remaining salt between layers.
Pour pan juice over layers.
Bake potatoes at 425°.
Slice beef and place on top of potatoes.
Stir together softened butter, minced garlic and parsley.
Spread over meat.
Heat at 425° for about 8 minutes.

title: breasts in wine sauce
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken and brown, on both sides, 12 to 16 minutes.
Add mushrooms, wine and herbes. Cook, covered, over low heat, 5 to 10 minutes or until hot. Serves 4.

title: mounds
directions: Mix all together and roll into small balls. Stick a toothpick in each ball. Melt 1/2 of a 1/4 pound of paraffin and 1 (6 ounce) chocolate chips. Dip balls and place on wax paper. (Can put the balls in refrigerator for 30 minutes before you dip them.)

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Smooth the bean dip over bottom of dish.
Mix the avocados with the mayonnaise.
Combine the sour cream with the taco seasoning.
Spread over the avocado mixture.
Season second layer with garlic salt, chili powder, pepper and Tabasco sauce to taste. Sprinkle with the olives and tomatoes and top with the cheese. Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight, covered with plastic wrap. This will meld flavors.
Serve with big Fritos chips.

title: vanilla butter frosting
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Stir in vanilla and milk; beat until frosting is smooth and spreading consistency.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: italian salad
directions: Cut up all vegetables in a large bowl, pour salad dressing all over the vegetables.
Let chill 2 hours or overnight and serve.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Cream water and shortening.
Combine salt, baking powder and flour and mix with shortening and water.

title: tomato dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until mixed well. Refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with raw cauliflower, carrots, peppers, celery, broccoli, etc.
(Sounds gross but is delicious!)

title: julia aling's crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add melted butter and eggs, then add sugar and salt.
Add flour last; do not overwork dough. Set in refrigerator overnight or several hours.
Pat out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut like pie into 16 pieces (approximately) and roll from broad end.
Let stand
until triple in size (couple of hours). Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese, then add remaining ingredients.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cheese, sugar and flour, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Pour mixture over crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and continue baking for 1 hour.
Loosen cake from rim, but cool before removing rim of pan. Chill.
Top with cherries, blueberries, etc.

title: blt bites
directions: Cut a thin slice off each tomato top. Scoop out and discard pulp. Invert the tomatoes on a paper towel to drain. In a bowl, combine all remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon into tomatoes. Refrigerate for several hours. Serve at parties, brunches and picnics. Always a hit.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Spread cubes in 8-inch round dish.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar.
Measure milk in 1-quart measuring cup.
Add butter; microwave on High about 4 minutes until butter is melted and milk warm.
Rapidly stir eggs into milk.
Pour over bread in dish. Microwave on Medium-high 9 to 12 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 6 minutes.
When cooked, center may still be slightly soft but will set as pudding cools.
Serve warm or cold.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour and baking soda.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes; let cool.
Mix the baking soda with 1 tablespoon water, then add 3 cups flour.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Mix cornmeal, eggs, soda, salt, milk and oil.
Grease 1 large iron skillet.
Pour 1/2 of cornmeal mixture into skillet.
Add ground beef mixture.
Cover with grated cheese.
Add rest of cornmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bierock casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and add onion; drain.
Add cabbage and soup and steam.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with one can of crescent rolls.
Top rolls with hamburger mixture.
Top with cheese.
Place second can of crescent rolls on top and pinch together.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Chill and serve. Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: broccoli with rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet saute the onion and celery in butter until vegetables are covered.
Cook broccoli according to directions; drain well.
Mix broccoli with soup and cheese.
Add celery and onion.
Stir in rice.
Season and mix well.
Put in a greased casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be mixed ahead and frozen.
Serves 6.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat three egg yolks (save whites for meringue).
Add sugar, flour and just enough milk to mix well.
Add remaining milk, vanilla and 3/4 cup coconut.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue of 3 egg whites; sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup coconut over meringue and bake at 400° until coconut is slightly browned.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake biscuits in a sack with next 3 ingredients.
Place sugared and spiced biscuit quarters in a Bundt pan and pour remaining sugar mixture from sack over top.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In largest cake pan, layer on bottom the shredded lettuce (tiny).
Next layer the chopped green onions.
Next, layer the celery and on top of celery, layer frozen peas.
Spread mayonnaise as next layer.
Break up in small pieces the bacon for the next layer.
And as the last layer, sprinkle the Cheddar cheese.
Put foil over and seal tightly.
Make the day before and keep sealed in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: dirty rice from dudley's
directions: Boil gizzards and livers in salt water until tender.
Remove and chop fine.
Reserve broth.
In a heavy Dutch oven, make a roux by heating the oil and flour.
Cook until dark brown.
Add chopped vegetables and cook until soft.
Add chopped chicken giblets.
Add reserved broth until covered by 1/2-inch.
Lower heat and cook until vegetables are tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Remove from heat and combine with cooked rice.
More broth may be added if the dressing is too dry.
Place in 3-quart casserole dish and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and crabmeat (pick out shell carefully), blending in horseradish to smooth consistency.
Spread on pretty plate with nice border.
Top with cocktail sauce and serve with crackers.
Very quick and easy.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Squeeze out excess water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Freeze on cookie sheet. After frozen, put in plastic bag.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, will not brown.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 12 regular muffin cups with paper liners; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
Mix applesauce, oil and eggs together.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until combined.
Mix in carrots and nuts.
Fill prepared muffin cups about 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
If desired, decorate tops of muffins by sifting confectioners sugar over desired stencil patterns such as letters or numbers.

title: earthquake chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chopped nuts in bottom of pan.
Spread coconut over nuts.
Pour cake mix over nuts and coconut.

title: coconut pie
directions: Bake at 350° until firm.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Stir all together.
Turn pot on high.
Cook 4 hours with lid on.
Remove lid and stir occasionally the first 4 hours.
Cook another 4 hours without the lid on.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: pineapple salad or christmas salad
directions: Mix lemon jello according to package directions.
Let cool. Mix the cream cheese and salad dressing together.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and whipping cream.
Mix in jello.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart dish (9 x 9-inch).
Refrigerate.
Mix up red jello according to package directions.
Let cool.
Pour over top of firmly set lemon jello mixture.
Refrigerate until red jello is firmly set (or overnight) before serving.

title: bayou blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a large, iron skillet.
Mix flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and milk and pour on top of butter (don't stir).
Mix together blackberries, 1 cup sugar and water and pour over mixture in skillet (don't stir).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Boil spaghetti in salt water until tender; drain.
Melt margarine in skillet and saute mushrooms.
Remove mushrooms. Blend flour with margarine; add evaporated milk, water (or juices from mushrooms), chopped green pepper, pimentos, cheese, Chicken Style, mushrooms and chicken style seasoning.
Mix together, then add spaghetti.

title: sausage bread
directions: Allow bread dough to thaw completely.
Brown sausage.
Add onions and bell pepper to sausage and saute until wilted.
Grease wooden cutting board or something similar in an area, approximately 10 x 13-inch.
Grease fingers.
Press bread dough into a rectangle approximately 10 x 13-inch.

title: "butterscotch pie"
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat egg yolks and add to cream and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked crust and add meringue.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion soup mix and 1/2 cup water.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour in 3 cans tomatoes and mash well.
Add vegetables.
Stir.
Add 2 cups water and let boil 15 minutes.
If too thick, add more water. Makes a lot but can be frozen in containers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Rinse and drain well. Then add chopped onion, bell pepper, tomato and cucumber.
Mix well with the spaghetti, then add the Salad Supreme and Zesty Italian salad dressing.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: mimere's banana toast
directions: Place banana slice on bread.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Place in toaster oven and toast to desired brownness.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Rinse.
Mix veggies, sauce and noodles in glass cake pan.
Mix in small amount of cheese.
Top with small amount of grated Mozzarella cheese and small amount of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter in microwave-safe dish.
Beat sugar, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
Combine flour, bran, oats and baking soda.
Stir into butter mixture.
Press half of dough into an 8 x 8-inch microsafe dish.
Shield corners of dish with foil to prevent overcooking.
Microwave at High power for 4 to 5 minutes, turning a quarter turn 3 times during baking.
Cool before cutting.
Repeat with second batch of dough.
To bake in oven, prepare the same and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: sour cream and chives dip
directions: In a small bowl with fork or wire whisk, mix the sour cream, chives, salt and red pepper.

title: salmon
directions: Mix salmon as you normally would to fry.
Substitute with fat-free crackers; add egg whites; throw the yolk away.
Use Teflon skillet; spray with Pam and cook on low heat until done. Turn heat up at end of cooking time in order to brown.

title: barry's brownies
directions: Sift whole wheat pastry flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in brown sugar well.
Beat in corn oil and eggs. Stir in chocolate chips.
Blend in the vanilla and chopped pecans. Pour into 9-inch square pan, greased and floured.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy; add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in butter; stir in chips and nuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: crisp sweet pickle chips
directions: Drain jar of dill chips.
Place the dill chips in a bowl and add sugar.
Stir.
Let set several hours.
Stir occasionally.
Put back into jar and cover pickles with liquid that has formed. Refrigerate.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: black-eyed peas italian style
directions: Soak black-eyed peas overnight or at least 10 hours.
Cover with water.
Drain water.
In large saucepan, place peas and cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour or until peas are tender.
Adjust seasoning; remove hot pepper. Serve as a side dish with chicken or fish or as part of a vegetarian meal with rice or pasta.

title: stacked salad
directions: Layer of lettuce, cut up eggs, rest of lettuce, sliced onions, bit pieces of tomato, green peas and crumbled bacon. Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together and put on top. Put grated cheese on top. Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: You should start by heating the oven to 450°.
Pour beef drippings or margarine to grease bottom and sides of a 9-inch square or round pan.
Place pan in oven to heat about 2 minutes. In small bowl, beat eggs slightly.
You should add remaining ingredients and beat until blended (do not overbeat).
Place bowl in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Take out and reheat.
You then pour batter into hot pan and bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for 15 minutes to golden brown. Best when served hot with warm gravy on top.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix salad dressing, lemon juice, dill weed, garlic salt and chopped nuts together.
Add mixture to cucumbers and onions and mix together.
Serve as cocktail sandwiches or use as a dip.

title: squaw corn
directions: Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Add bacon to pan and fry. When bacon is browned, drain grease.
Add onion and green pepper to bacon; fry until vegetables are almost soft.
Add corn; fry until heated.
Add beaten eggs and scramble.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: raisin molasses bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt the butter.
When cooled slightly, stir in sugar, slightly beaten egg, molasses and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Add raisins and walnuts to this mixture.
Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch cookie sheet and bake about 12 minutes.
Cut into bars when cool and dust with sugar and cinnamon.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and salt until lemon colored.
Add melted butter, flour, Milnot, vanilla and 1 cup coconut.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on top.
Cook as custard pie.
Bake in pie shell until done at 375°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and onions in shortening.
Add pinto beans and chili powder.
Top with your favorite corn bread batter. Bake until done and brown.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Toss all vegetables together in a large mixing bowl.
Combine the vinegar, oil, sugar and salt together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour hot over the vegetables and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Cut
tomatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices and arrange in a large shallow dish;
set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar;
cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over tomato slices.
Cover
and
marinate
in
refrigerator several hours. Yields 6 servings.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix ingredients and put in large square dish or pan and freeze.
Serve partially frozen.

title: ham and broccoli sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt 1 1/2 teaspoons margarine over medium heat.
Whisk in flour and whisk continuously for 1 minute. Slowly whisk in the milk and stir constantly until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese and pepper.
When cheese is melted, add sour cream and mix well.
Set aside.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain fat, add to pot containing all other ingredients except beans.
Cook for 3 hours.
Add beans last 1/2 hour.

title: barbecue sauce recipe
directions: In saucepan, combine water, ketchup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, celery seed and bottled hot pepper sauce. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt to taste and cayenne to test for hotness.

title: rockin' chair cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix pecans, flour and butter (do not melt). Press in bottom of glass pan. Bake for 15 minutes; cool. Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pecan mixture. Mix pudding and milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Let chill 1 hour.

title: crazy corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place liners in cups of muffin tins. Set aside.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Toss together with a fork.
Add butter, milk, sour cream and maple syrup to bowl; blend with a spoon.
Even when this batter is blended, it will still have a few lumps.
Crack eggs in a separate bowl and whisk to blend.
Add eggs to batter with pecan pieces.
Blend.
Spoon batter into muffin cups to 3/4 full.
Bake in oven for 25 minutes.
Cool on cooling rack.
Let cool completely, if you are going to freeze them.
Wrap in plastic wrap; then freeze.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces.
Shake biscuit in plastic bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Shake until all covered.
Grease a Bundt pan or angel food pan with butter.
Place 1/2 cup pecans in bottom of pan.
Arrange biscuit pieces in pan.
Sprinkle more pecans among pieces.
Melt butter and add 1 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well and pour slowly over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.

title: cherries jubilee* * * * *
directions: Ellie is an old high school friend who is now married to my brother.
She thinks she can't cook, but I've never had a bad meal there yet.
The Cherries Jubilee recipe came from the chef at the Officer's Club on Etain Air Force Base in France.

title: pork chops in mushroom gravy
directions: Brown pork chops in margarine.
Add mushroom soup and water to cover pork chops.
Slice potatoes, carrots and onion.
Add to pork chops and add more water if needed.
May be cooked in oven (350° until potatoes are done), electric skillet or crock-pot.

title: raspberry chicken
